title: hot chicken salad
directions: Saute celery and onion. Mix all ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch pan. May top with 1 cup crushed corn flakes or 1/2 cup sliced almonds or buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in saucepan until water is gone.
Pour rice into 2-quart casserole.
Add vanilla, sugar and evaporated milk. Stir. Add whole milk.
Stir again and sprinkle cinnamon on top. Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour.
Stir and bake
until puffy.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Bake pastry shells according to package directions.
In medium saucepan, cook pepper in butter until tender.
Add soup, milk, chicken and pimiento.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into warm pastry shells.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and pour into a large baking dish or pan.
Mix well together in a bowl the flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and milk.
Pour into dish. Add the canned peaches with liquid. Sprinkle sugar lightly over top. Bake 45 minutes or until brown at 325°.

title: peach fluff
directions: Fold Jell-O into cottage cheese.
Chop peaches and bananas; fold into Jell-O mixture.
Mix Cool Whip into mixture.
Chill.

title: cheeseburger quiche
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain well.
In bowl, beat together milk, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Add 1 cup grated cheese and beef and onion mixture to bowl.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese just before removing from oven.
Done when knife inserted comes out clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: yummies
directions: Beat egg white.
Add vanilla, then sugar.
Add pecans.
Drop one teaspoon at a time onto foil covered cookie sheet.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and let remain in oven 30 minutes longer.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar, flour, milk and eggs in pan.
Put remaining sugar in skillet to caramelize.
Cook both pans at the same time, stirring.
When sugar melts and turns light brown, the other mixture should begin to thicken.
Pour caramelized sugar into pudding; stir until thick.
Remove and add 1 teaspoon oleo and vanilla.
Pour into cooled, baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: chewy date nut strips
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Beat in the eggs.
Stir in dates, nuts and vanilla.
Stir in the flour mixed with baking powder.
Spoon the batter into a 9-inch square pan and bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
While still warm, cut into strips and roll in granulated sugar.

title: chili
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook 1 hour.
Add kidney beans. Simmer 2 hours.

title: no peek beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir together well. Cover and cook on low 8 to 12 hours (high 4 to 6 hours).
Serves 4.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all together well.
Chill 30 minutes.
Shape into balls and place on baking sheet.
Freeze.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: onion soup meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs, ketchup, water and soup mix. Add bread crumbs and ground beef. Mix well. Shape into a loaf and place on shallow pan. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin loaf cake
directions: In bowl, cream butter until light.
Gradually beat in sugar. Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger and cloves.
Add to creamed butter mixture alternately with canned pumpkin.
When batter is well mixed, add chocolate morsels and 1/2 nuts.
Put in greased and floured loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) and scatter remaining walnuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake springs back.
Allow cake to cool for 15 minutes.
Turn out on rack to complete cooling.

title: sweet potato honey rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Heat remaining 1/4 cup water, sugar, 3 tablespoons butter and salt in small pan.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs, sweet potatoes and vanilla.
Combine 1 1/4 cups flour, yeast and sweet potato mixture in mixing bowl.
Beat at low speed for 1/2 minute.
Then beat on high for 2 minutes, scraping sides of bowl.
By hand, stir in enough remaining flour to make a moderate stiff dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic (about 8 minutes).
Place in greased bowl, turning dough to grease top.
Cover and let rise until almost double (about 1 hour).

title: mocha pudding cake
directions: Combine flour, 2/3 cup sugar, 1/4 cup cocoa, coffee granules, baking powder and salt in a bowl; stir well.
Combine milk, oil and vanilla in a bowl; add to dry ingredients and stir well. Spoon batter into an 8-inch square baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Combine remaining 1/3 cup sugar and remaining 2 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle over batter.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over batter (do not stir).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until cake springs back when lightly touched in center.
Serve warm, topped with ice milk.
Yields 9 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well and roll into balls. Bake at 325 degrees.

title: hot tuna
directions: Add Miracle Whip and mustard until smooth.
Good served as an appetizer with crackers.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter.
Add
onion and bell pepper and cook until clear. Add chuck and brown slightly.
Add soup, mushrooms and seasonings;
simmer
slowly
or 20 minutes.
Turn off heat and blend
in
sour
cream.
Serve
over rice or toast strips. Strips of pimento may be added for garnish.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain again.
In bowl, stir together the next 7 ingredients.
Add macaroni, celery, eggs and cucumber; toss to coat well.
Cover; chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: blue cheese burgers
directions: Cook onion in heated butter in a large, heavy frying pan until lightly browned.
Remove from heat.
Set aside.

title: long lasting snow
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons soak flakes with 1/2 cup lukewarm water, in a large bowl.
Beat mixture with a rotary beater until suds are thick and dry.
Slowly add 1/3 cup instant laundry starch, beating constantly.

title: holiday fruit cake
directions: Butter a spring-form pan or 9-inch tube pan.
Line with waxed paper.
Butter again.
Sift flour and soda.
Combine eggs, mincemeat, condensed milk, fruit and nuts.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Pour into pan; bake in slow oven at 300° for 2 hours or until center springs back when touched (top is golden brown). Cool.
Turn out and remove waxed paper.

title: baby wipes from the tightwad gazette
directions: Cut roll of towels in half so that you have 2 short rolls; remove cardboard center.
Mix liquids in a plastic container (such as an old baby wipes container).
Place 1 of the half-roll paper towels into container.
Put lid on tightly.
Turn container upside-down to let towels thoroughly soak.
When ready to use, pull towels from center of the roll.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat well.
Add milk and vanilla and beat until well blended.
Pour in dish and sprinkle paprika or cinnamon on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Let vinegar, oil, sugar, pepper and salt come to a boil; cool. When cool, pour over the vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: fluffy grasshoppie pie
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press firmly on bottom and up side of buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Chill.
Meanwhile, in a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon and liqueurs.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chill 20 minutes; pile into crust.
Chill or freeze 4 hours or until set.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate or freeze leftovers.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix all except nuts.
Butter and flour Bundt pan.
Pour nuts in bottom of pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let set 10 minutes, then pour glaze over.
Do not remove from pan.

title: early american casserole
directions: Brown crumbled beef; add onion and cook until soft.
Add limas, corn, soup and seasoning.
Simmer until vegetables are tender, stirring to prevent sticking.
Add water if necessary.

title: tom cruise cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine crushed pineapple and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Cool slightly.
When baked cake has cooled, poke holes in it with a fork.
Pour pineapple mixture over it.
Prepare pudding mix according to package directions.
Cool.
Spread over top of pineapple.
Chill.
Just before serving, cover with whipped topping and sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: smoke turkey
directions: Dissolve Tender Quick in water.
Add meat, enough that it is all covered with brine.
Let set 2 days.
Drain.
Rub on liquid smoke and lay overnight.
Ready to bake, can or freeze.
This recipe may have to be doubled or tripled for large turkey.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix together pineapple and gelatin.
Bring to boil, let cool and add
buttermilk,
whipped
topping, coconut and nuts. Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and chill until set.

title: mounds
directions: Combine sugar, oleo, milk, coconut and pecans; roll into balls.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in a double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate, using toothpicks.
Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: mac and cheese tomato soup
directions: Boil macaroni and strain.
Combine tomato soup with sugar, butter, milk, Worcestershire and cheese mix in saucepan and heat until butter melts.
Add macaroni and stir all ingredients.
Serve and enjoy.
Cooked hot dogs may also be added.

title: forget them cookies
directions: First, turn on oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Beat in sugar.
Continue beating to stiff peaks.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Drop by teaspoon onto foil.
Turn off oven, then put cookies into oven and forget them!
Let them stay overnight or up to 12 hours.
Good! Good!

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well and store; use 2 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: chocolate chocolate
directions: Heat 1st
4 ingredients in heavy large saucepan to 130° (using meat
thermometer),
stirring
as it heats.
Whisk in 9 eggs, one at
a
time.
Pour
into an 11-inch spring-form pan (buttered, lined with
foil and buttered again).
Bake at 250° for 2 hours. Cool
and refrigerate.
Make at least 8 hours or one full day before serving.

title: webb's "best fish ever"
directions: If fish is not to be cooked immediately, soak in any kind of milk in the refrigerator until cooking time.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Melt butter and
pour
over
stuffing.
Put
half of stuffing in bottom of 13
x
9-inch
baking
dish.
Next
chicken.
Blend together soups, cream and
broth.
Pour over chicken; top with rest of stuffing. (I mix all together in
a bowl and top with a few crumbs.) Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swiss stuffed peppers
directions: Cook rice, clean peppers and precook peppers in boiling salt water for 5 minutes and drain.
Cook bacon until crisp. Drain and crumble.
Cook onion in 2 tablespoons of bacon grease until tender.

title: in advance breakfast
directions: Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard together.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour into a deep 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until set, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: In a large pan or pot, melt 2 tablespoons butter or margarine. Add and saute green onions, garlic, parsley and mushrooms.
Add clams and wine.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: healthy cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat oil and sugars until blended. Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add combined flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in combined oats and raisins. Mix well.
Drop by rounded Tbsp. onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to rack.

title: tea cakes by grand nana
directions: Cream sugar, butter, shortening and eggs. Mix all ingredients together. Add the flour in small amounts at a time until dough is thick enough to roll out. Roll out thin. Cut into 1/2-inch biscuits. Bake at 250° until done.

title: joe's quick chicken
directions: In a mixing bowl, pour shaken dressing (for less fat skim or drain oil from bottle).
Dip chicken into dressing, then corn flake crumbs.
Put in pan, uncovered.
Pour extra dressing over chicken. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix well and pour into flat jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: In large kettle, saute until lightly browned.
Drain and discard fat.
Add onions and garlic.
Saute until onions are limp. Stir in tomatoes, breaking them into small pieces.
Add broth, wine and basil.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool; transfer to large bowl and refrigerate.
Skim fat from surface; discard.
Return soup to kettle.
Stir in macaroni, zucchini, green pepper and
parsley.
Simmer covered 15 minutes or until macaroni and vegetables are tender-crisp.
Serve with cheese.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar

title: soy sauce chicken
directions: Place eggs in bowl with flour in shallow dish.
Dip pieces in eggs, then flour.
Be sure pieces are well coated with flour. Place in oil (medium-high temperature).
Add chicken a few pieces at a time.
Cook about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
In saucepan, mix together sugar and soy sauce.
Bring to boil.
Dip pieces in sauce while still hot.
Drain on rack.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook for 15 minutes (until crisp and crunchy).

title: vegetarian chili soup
directions: Add chicken broth to get the consistency of the soup you like.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and milk.
Beat well, then add flour, cornmeal and lemon juice.
Pour mixture into pie shell; bake at 350° until done, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange salad(tasty enough to be used as a dessert.)
directions: Pour boiling water over the tapiocas and jello.
Mix, then cook until thick.
Cool.
Add mandarin oranges (cut them in small pieces) and pineapple.
Fold in the whipped topping.
Chill.

title: party pink pineapple punch
directions: Have ingredients well chilled, including ginger ale.
Combine all ingredients except ginger ale.
For lively bubbles, add ginger ale at last minute.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar together.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix in.
Add vanilla and zucchini.
Pour into greased pan (10 x 15 x 2-inch).
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until done in center at 350°.
If desired frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: taco meat loaf
directions: Place hamburger and diced onions in skillet. Brown and drain. Set aside.
Combine soups, taco sauce, seasoning, tomato sauce, water and rice.
Heat over medium heat. Add hamburger mixture. Pour all in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle the Doritos on top. Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Take cover off and top with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: strawberry marbled cheesecake
directions: In blender container, combine strawberries and cornstarch; blend until smooth.
In heavy saucepan, over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened.
Add food coloring if desired.
Reserve 1/3 cup sauce; cool.
Chill remaining sauce.
Preheat oven to 300°. Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in Eagle Brand until smooth.
Add eggs and ReaLemon brand; mix well.
Spoon half the batter into prepared pan.
Spoon half the reserved strawberry sauce in small amounts over batter. Repeat, ending with sauce.
With knife, cut through batter to marble.
Bake 50 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Chill. Remove side of spring-form.
Serve with chilled strawberry sauce. Refrigerate leftovers.
Prep time:
30 minutes.
Total time:
3 1/2 hours.
Makes one 9-inch cheesecake.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients (except carrots) together.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add to cooked carrots.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: heavenly carrots
directions: Place carrots in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in croutons and cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over carrots.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 400°.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix together in a large pot.
Bring to a boil and simmer for about an hour.

title: speedy baked beans
directions: Saute bacon and onion until bacon is crisp and onion is yellow.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole (7 1/2-inches).
Bake, uncovered, until beans are brown and bubbly.
Serve hot.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: linguini with white clam sauce
directions: Heat oil in medium size saucepan. Add onions and cook until clear in color.
(Be careful not to burn onion.)
Add clams with liquid.

Add stock. Add garlic and herbs. Add vermouth. Simmer for 10 minutes. Cook linguini as per package instructions (best when al dente). Serve with freshly grated Romano or Parmesan cheese. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and shortening together and beat.
Dissolve soda in hot water and add (that is all the liquid).
Add vanilla, flour and chopped nuts.
Shape into balls.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Blend together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°, then cool.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until tender and drain.
Saute onion, celery and garlic in butter until transparent.
Add 1/2 cup of flour to vegetables and stir into a paste.
Add broth and milk; stir until smooth.
Add cubed Velveeta cheese and broccoli; simmer.
Do not boil until cheese melts.

title: blueberry sour cream cake
directions: Coat berries with flour.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and sour cream.
Add lemon rind and beat well.
Add dry ingredients. Fold in blueberries.
Pour batter in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10 minutes in pan, then turn out on rack.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: caribbean fudge pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat in large bowl the margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add chocolate, coffee and rum extracts; mix well.
Stir in flour and chopped walnuts.
Pour into pastry shell. Decorate top of pie with walnut halves.
Bake in lower third of oven 25 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Makes 10 servings.

title: pasta-in-a-pot
directions: Cook
the first 7 ingredients; simmer 20 minutes.
Cook and drain shells.
Put half of shells in the bottom of a large casserole.
Put half of the sauce over the shells.
Spread half of the sour cream, then Provolone cheese over all.
Repeat the layers, ending with Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cheese melts and
lightly browns.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and syrup.
Pour over well beaten eggs.
Add vanilla and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Put nuts on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 more minutes.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix all ingredients (except strawberry preserves).
Grease a mold with mayonnaise.
Insert a small glass that has been coated with mayonnaise into center of mold.
Pour cheese mixture into mold.
Chill in refrigerator until ready for use.
Unmold onto serving dish.
Fill center of mold with strawberry preserves. Serve with crackers.
If desired, after unmolding cheese ring, sprinkle with chopped pecans or walnuts.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Combine lemon juice and milk.
Add egg yolks; beat well until blended.
Pour into chilled crust.
Add sugar to egg whites.
Beat with mixer until stiff.
Pile lightly onto pie filling.
Bake at 325° until meringue is slightly browned.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch well, then add water and cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Cool 10 minutes and add strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream, Dream Whip or Cool Whip as it is served.

title: pizza dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in pizza pan.
Pour chili sauce over cheese.
Put peppers and onions on sauce, then cheese.
Place black olives on.
Serve with chips or crackers.
Refrigerate until one hour before you serve.
You can use a good jar of salsa instead of the chili sauce.

title: deluxe fruit salad
directions: Mix together, juice and all, in a large bowl.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
I make this at special times of the year.

title: green apple pie
directions: Peel, slice and core apples.
Fill pie crust with apples to desired depth.
Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt; pour over apples and dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Seal edges and brush with melted butter.
Make a small opening in center of top crust to allow steam to escape.
Cook until apples are tender and juice bubbles and crust is golden brown.
Bake at 350°.

title: mom's cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Combine cucumber and onion slices and salt.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Drain and add the sour cream, vinegar and sugar.
Taste and adjust seasonings.

title: cheese log
directions: Grate cheeses.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form into a log with wax paper.
Roll in pecans.

title: italian chicken pasta
directions: In small bowl, combine the flour and spices.
Add chicken cubes; toss until well coated.
Heat oil in skillet on medium high heat.
Add chicken; brown on all sides.
Drain any leftover oil, then stir in sauce and heat through.
Serve over hot pasta. Serves 3 or 4.
Double if needed.

title: perky cinnamon apple juice
directions: Put spices in basket; perk juice and ginger ale through perking cycle of a 30 cup pot.
Make the house smell wonderful. Great for a Christmas party.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Cook milk, flour, lemon juice and butter until thick.
Add along with other ingredients to the salmon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mud pud pie
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: layered salad
directions: Drain English peas and put them aside.
Wash vegetables and drain.
Break lettuce into bite size pieces.
Place in a large bowl 1/2 of the lettuce, then put a layer of broccoli and then a layer of cauliflower.
Next put a layer of peas and a layer of cucumbers. Top with the remaining lettuce.
Mix up a package of Hidden Valley Ranch salad dressing and pour over salad.
Top with onion slices then cheese.
You can add bacon bits if you like.
Chill and serve.

title: cheese blintzs
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Roll flat with rolling pin lightly. Beat together cream cheese, egg and sugar.
Spread on bread and roll up.
Roll in melted butter, then roll in sugar and cinnamon mix.
Slice into 2 to 4 slices as desired and freeze on a cookie sheet.
They can then be placed in a Ziploc bag.
Bake as needed at 400° until done, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: moo goo gai pan
directions: Slice chicken 1/4 thick and
cut into 1 inch pieces.
Sprinkle with soy sauce, white pepper and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Mix together chicken broth, 2 tablespoons soy sauce and 2 tablespoons cornstarch and set aside.

title: chicken costa brava
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Sprinkle chicken with salt. Brown chicken in oil.
Combine spices; sprinkle over chicken.
Add garlic and onion.
Saute.
Add reserved juice with next 4 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.

title: crunchy party chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potato chips.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle potato chips on top.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: baked spiced peaches
directions: Set out 4 small, individual baking dishes or a shallow baking dish.
Drain peach halves, reserving syrup.
Arrange peaches, cut side up, in baking dishes.
Pour over peaches a mixture of peach syrup, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, basting 2 or 3 times.
Remove from oven.
Increase oven temperature to 400°.
Sprinkle over peaches a mixture of corn flakes, pecans and butter or margarine.
Return to oven; bake 5 minutes longer.
Serve peaches warm with cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Place all ingredients into mixing bowl; combine thoroughly. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the topping ingredients.

title: ricotta cheese cake(sugar-free and crustless)
directions: Pam spray 9-inch glass pie plate.
Sprinkle Knox gelatine over the 1/2 cup pineapple juice to soften.
Combine all ingredients in blender, then blend until almost smooth.
Pour into pie pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
It is done when sides are lightly browned and center almost firm.
Chill before serving. Can garnish with cinnamon if desired.

title: quiche
directions: Beat together eggs, half and half, salt and pepper.
Toss together meat, cheese and flour.
Add to egg mixture and pour into crust.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain fruit and cut cherries in quarters.
Put fruit in large mixing bowl.
Add cherries, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Mix and serve.

title: easy apple bread
directions: Combine biscuit mix and sugar.
Combine egg, oil and milk. Beat well.
Stir in biscuit mix and sugar.
Mix well.
Stir in apple.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: polo beet salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar and sugar; add beets, onion, pepper and seasonings.
Chill several hours and serve cold.

title: sweet salad
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients and refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions; cool.
Mix 1 large can crushed pineapple and 1 cup sugar.
Boil for 10 minutes; let cool.
While still warm, put on cooled cake.
Mix 2 boxes instant pineapple pudding with 3 1/2 cups milk.
Spread on cake. Spread 1 large tub Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake in a 325° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes a very big batch.

title: tuna mold
directions: Heat soup; stir in lemon juice, mustard and salt together. Chill.
Add mayonnaise.
Fold in onions, celery, tuna and any vegetables you would like.
Gently fill mold.
Chill several hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown beef on all sides in hot oil.
Add onion, tomatoes, tapioca, broth, garlic, parsley, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over casserole.
Cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Add vegetables; bake for 1 hour or until vegetables are done.

title: western barbecue sauce
directions: Wash the bones and discard excess fat.
Mix all ingredients together except the Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, horseradish and Tabasco sauce.
Simmer for 4 hours.
Chill and let stand several hours or overnight in the refrigerator.
Skim any fat off the top. Heat sauce and discard the bones.
Press all the pulp through a strainer.
(You can skip this part if you don't mind chunks in your sauce.)
Add the last 4 ingredients.
Taste and add more seasoning if desired.
If you like it really hot, add 1/4 cup jalapeno slices.
Serve over rice, on ribs, chicken or hamburgers. Makes one quart.

title: waffles
directions: When I first came upon this recipe, I thought of my grandparents.
They were farmers.
They both had to get jobs to supplement their income when their children got older, but their hearts were never into it.

title: payday bars
directions: Mix together dry cake mix, 1/2 cup melted oleo and eggs. Makes a stiff dough.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; cover with marshmallows.
Bake for 5 minutes more.

title: soft chicken tacos
directions: In frying pan, add drained canned chicken. Heat through for 5 to 6 minutes (do not let it dry out). Add salsa (you may need more or less than 4 ounces) and heat an additional 5 minutes. Heat corn tortillas on a griddle or in a pan. Add chicken mixture to tortillas and shredded lettuce and tomato and anything else that sounds good. Makes 4 servings.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.
You can use low-fat sour cream and cottage cheese.

title: liver, onions and tomatoes
directions: Combine the flour, salt (optional) and pepper; dredge the liver in the flour mixture.
In a heavy saute pan, heat half of the oil and cook the liver over medium-high heat until just cooked and tender, 1 to 2 minutes each side.
(Do not overcook.)
Remove liver to a serving dish and keep warm.
Add the remaining oil to the pan along with the onion slices.
Cook, stirring, over medium heat until the onions are soft and golden, about 7 to 10 minutes. Add the tomato slices and cook 1 to 2 more minutes.
Return the cooked liver to the pan to reheat.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and serve.

title: chuck wagon mac
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
Brown meat; add celery, pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add corn, tomato paste, salt and pepper, then macaroni and cheese.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: favorite chicken casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, spread chicken pieces on bottom. In separate bowl, combine sour cream, cream of chicken and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken. Spread out stuffing over sauce. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Remove pan from oven and add cheese on top. Bake until cheese is melted.

title: lillian's hollandaise sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, place the cream cheese that has been softened to room temperature.
Blend in the egg yolks, one at a time.
Slowly stir in the lemon juice and a dash of salt.
Let mixture thicken over low heat, stirring constantly.

title: party punch
directions: Dilute juices with 3 cans each of water.
Mix together.
Place half of mixture in a punch bowl.
Add half of sodas.
Repeat for second bowl of punch.

title: a chocolate chip kiss
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and salt.
Fold in pecans and chocolate morsels. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto foil-lined cookie sheets.
Put in oven; turn heat off and leave overnight.
Store in airtight container. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and flour, corn and milk; melt butter in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: crunchy cheese nibbles
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients.
Shape dough into 3/4 inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake at 375 F for 5-7 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove to a wire rack.
Serve warm.
Yield about 3 dozen.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and fold in the biscuits.
Let sit in refrigerator or until bread has soaked up the milk-egg mixture. Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart buttered dish and dot with butter.
Fruit or raisins may be folded into mixture. Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve hot from oven.
It's great topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Slice venison into thin strips.
Coat strips in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown the strips in as much margarine as needed.
Take out and set aside.
In the same skillet saute onions, sliced mushrooms and minced garlic in margarine.
Add the flour to the mixture, then gradually pour in the beef broth, stirring until smooth.
Bring this to a boil and simmer 5 minutes over low heat.
Add wine, sour cream and dill.
Put the venison strips in and heat thoroughly. Serve over hot buttered noodles.

title: orange gumdrop cookies
directions: Beat eggs with water until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and salt, beating until light and fluffy.
Mix candy, nuts, coconut and flour.
Stir into egg mixture.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In Dutch oven, cook over medium heat until peanuts begin to crack open, then add baking soda and stir in well and fast. Remove from heat and pour on aluminum foil. Cool and break in pieces.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut ribs in serving pieces; sprinkle generously with garlic salt on both sides.
Place single layer on baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over ribs and bake in 325° oven 2 1/2 hours.
Turn ribs over every half hour and baste with sauce.

title: peanut butter fudge cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake as directed.
Cool.
Spread peanut butter over cake.
Combine cocoa and butter and boil for 1 1/2 minutes. Pour chocolate over peanut butter.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: janet's franks and beer sauce
directions: Cut wieners in 1-inch pieces.
Bring beer, sugar and Tabasco to a rapid boil.
Drop in wieners.
Stir constantly until all liquid is gone and glaze forms on wieners.
Remove from pan and serve hot.

title: crunchy peanut biscuit ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 12 cup fluted tube pan, 2 1/2-quart ring mold or 10-inch tube pan (don't use kind with removeable bottom).
In saucepan (or microwave), melt margarine; stir in nuts, brown sugar and syrup.
Pour about 1/4 cup sugar mixture into greased pan (spray Pam works fine).

title: strawberry cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, break the cake into small pieces. Spread small container of Cool Whip on top.
Mix with mixer large Cool Whip, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until sugar is dissolved.
Spread as second layer.
Mix strawberries and glaze together; spread over second layer.

title: mint honey chicken
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: beef-bean casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion in skillet.
Add ketchup, vinegar, brown sugar and salt.
Add all beans.
Turn into large casserole dish; top with bacon strips.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour. Serves 12 to 15.

title: spaghetti amore
directions: Brown meat with onion, pepper and garlic; drain off fat.
Add soups and water.
Heat.
Place cooked spaghetti in greased casserole.
Pour meat mixture over; stir in 1/2 cup grated cheese lightly.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and dry ingredients. Roll into balls, walnut size.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture. Place on cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Blend 1 1/2 cups of milk with butter and sugar.
Bring to boil; add 3 tablespoons of cornstarch to 1/2 cup milk and add to mixture.
Bring to boil and set aside.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with nutmeg.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: christmas cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries.
Add the sugar, pineapple and marshmallows.
Whip the cream.
Fold all ingredients together gently.
Refrigerate.

title: fisherman's pie
directions: Cook fish in boiling salted water until it flakes; drain. Break into bite-size pieces.
Combine 2 eggs, milk and seasonings. Blend well.
Add 2 tablespoons butter; stir in fish and beans. Pour into greased baking dish.
Combine potatoes with 1 egg and 2 tablespoons butter.
Spread potatoes to cover mixture in baking dish.
Brush with remaining butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, grated cheese, mayonnaise, onion and water chestnuts together.
Top with crackers and oleo.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Coal chicken legs with bread crumbs.
Arrange legs in a circle with the thick end to the outside of the dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 5 to 7 minutes.
Spread spaghetti sauce evenly over chicken.
Place cheese on top of sauce.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on 70% power for 4 to 7 minutes.
Use a 2 quart casserole dish.
If using oven, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tomato-peanut butter soup
directions: Braise onion in olive oil.
Puree tomatoes in blender and add chicken broth.
Add creamy peanut butter to taste.
Simmer 30 minutes; serve with toasted dill garlic bread.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Put in casserole dish in layers: potatoes, onion and creamed corn, until used up.
Salt and pepper to taste and pour in milk and melted margarine.
Cover and bake in a 2-quart casserole at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Take one large field, half-a-dozen children, two or three small dogs, a pinch of brook and some pebbles.
Mix the children and dogs well together; put them on the field, stirring constantly.
Pour the brook over the pebbles; sprinkle the field with flowers. Spread over all a deep blue sky and bake in the sun.
When brown, set away to cool in a bathtub.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Grease a 10x9-inch pie plate.
Place all ingredients in a blender and blend until mixed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tomato fritters
directions: Mix ingredients into tomatoes.
Heat approximately 1/4-inch grease in pan.
Fry until brown.
Makes 8 fritters.

title: lime pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, lime and water in crock for 24 hours.
Then, rinse 2 or 3 times in cold water.
Again soak 3 hours in cold water; drain.
Place spices in tied cloth bag and heat with vinegar, salt, sugar and coloring until sugar is dissolved. Pour over drained cucumbers and let soak overnight.
In morning, heat slowly until heated through.
Let boil slowly for 35 minutes. Place in jars and seal hot.

title: judy's brownies
directions: Melt
butter
and
add cocoa.
Add eggs and sugar; beat well. Add
vanilla,
salt, flour and nuts.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix well. Drop by spoonful into hot oil and fry until brown.

title: reese's peanut butter bar
directions: Mix ingredients and place in a pan.
Melt chocolate chips; spread over top.
Let chill.

title: fried green tomatoes(club member: lee higginbotham)
directions: Mix together flour, meal, salt and pepper.
Mix buttermilk and eggs.
Dip tomato slices in batter, then in flour mixture.
Fry in oil; drain well.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cover and cook onion in butter in saucepan over low heat until tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
Add broth, water, bay leaf, pepper and thyme.
Heat to boiling; cover and reduce heat to simmer 15 minutes.

title: skillet meal
directions: Scrub potatoes; cook in boiling salted water until tender. Drain and let cool 15 minutes.
In medium skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Peel and cube potatoes.
Add potatoes, onion, salt and pepper to skillet. Cook, stirring, until potatoes are brown and onion is tender. Sprinkle cheese evenly over top.
Break eggs into skillet, stirring constantly, over low heat until done.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute pepper, onion and celery in 1 stick of butter.
Mix remaining ingredients except other stick of butter and crackers. Put in casserole dish.
Melt remaining butter.
Sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken, broccoli and cheese dinner
directions: Boil chicken until done; let cool and tear in small pieces. Steam broccoli until tender.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and water.
Place 1/2 of cheese in saucepan with milk; melt slowly. Do not boil.
Place chicken in casserole dish; layer with broccoli, soup and cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes until hot.
You may add more cheese if desired.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: pumpkin bread(makes 3 to 4 loaves)
directions: Mix in order.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or a little longer at 300° in greased bread pans.

title: thai-style chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together the lime juice, salt, chili powder, cilantro and mint; mix in the onions and mayonnaise.
Stir in chicken.
Chill well.
Serve over lettuce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sidewalk chalk(made from eggshells)
directions: Will need clean, smooth rock, 2 small dishes, spoon and strip of paper towel.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skin until done, but firm.
Cool, peel and grate on coarse grater.
Melt butter and cheese.
Add all ingredients and mix.
Put in casserole; dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Best served 15 minutes after coming from oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: olive spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, chill. Serve with cocktail bread or crackers. I like it on wheat thins.

title: berry dips
directions: Mix Cool Whip, orange peel, berries and yogurt.
Dip berries, fruits and cake cubes into mix.
Makes 5 cups.
Store in refrigerator.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Combine evaporated milk, water, cheese and butter and heat to boiling until cheese melts.
Add onion, tuna, salt, eggs, macaroni and bread crumbs.
Put into loaf pan and bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Boil the chicken for 45 minutes; cut into cubes. Boil the water for egg noodles. Combine noodles, chicken and cream of mushroom soup in a bowl; mix well. Put into a 9 x 11 casserole dish; top with cheese. In a separate bowl, melt the butter and mix with bread crumbs. Sprinkle this mixture on top of the cheese. Place in the oven and bake at 350° until cheese has melted.

title: summer casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine vegetables, chicken broth and half of cheese in a bowl.
Place in ungreased casserole.
Bake covered for 1 hour.
Test carrots for tenderness.
Add pasta and mix thoroughly.
Top with remaining cheese and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: Simmer for 1 hour.
Pour into glass container and let stand for 12 hours.
Add 3 cups vodka and 4 teaspoons vanilla.
Mix and let stand 1/2 hour.
(Can be doubled.)

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Mix diced apricots and boiling water and let stand 15 minutes. Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs; add apricots and water to mixture.
Stir in flour, salt and baking soda.
Add nuts to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 small or 1 large loaf.

title: chocolate cherry cordial muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease twelve muffin cups or line with cupcake liners.
In large bowl combine flour, granulated sugar, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in 1 3/4 cups chocolate morsels and cherries; set aside.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: veal scappini
directions: Pound veal; heat 6 tablespoons butter and add veal.
Brown fast.
Add sherry and cook a few seconds and remove from heat. Melt remaining butter; add flour and stir.
Meanwhile, bring water and milk to a boil and add bouillon cubes.
Add this to butter and flour.
Stir until thick and smooth.
Season with nutmeg and pepper.

title: mom tait's he man casserole
directions: Brown steak in hot oil over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic; cook until golden.
Stir in flour.
Add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Turn into greased 3-quart casserole. Bake uncovered at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry tossed salad
directions: Mix oil, sugar, vinegar, salt, paprika and pepper in a jar with a lid; shake well to make dressing.
Toss remaining ingredients with dressing.

title: big party punch
directions: Combine juices and sugar; stir until mixed well.
Chill for about 1 hour.
Place ice in punch bowl.
Carefully pour ginger ale in the bowl (at edge of bowl).
Add orange slices and cherries to float on top.
Makes about eighty 7-ounce servings.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Blend
sugar, mayonnaise and cream cheese until smooth. Fold in
whipped
cream.
Fold in drained fruit, cherries and marshmallows.
Pour
into
container (the empty fruit cocktail can makes
pretty
slices) and freeze.
Slice and serve while still slightly frozen.
Try adding other fruit (bananas, chunk pineapple, etc.) and nuts next time.

title: apple-sausage oven pancake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Brown sausage as directed on package.
Beat Bisquick, cinnamon, milk and egg with a spoon until smooth.
Stir in apples.
Pour into baking dish.
Arrange sausage on top.
Bake until lightly brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: steak with garlic sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce and steak sauce.
Stir until mixed.
Bring to boiling point.
Remove from heat.
Place steak on broiler pan. Brush with steak sauce mixture.
Broil for 5 minutes longer or to desired doneness.
Yields 4 servings.

title: wood's applejack-apple pie(in honor of jenny kate)
directions: Make your favorite pastry for a 2-crust, 9-inch pie.
Roll out 1/2 the pastry to fit the pie plate; flute edges.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Add 8 ounces cream cheese and butter.
Mix well.
Place in greased casserole and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese (generously).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes, until lightly brown.
Serves 10.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as it says on the package.
Add cream of mushroom soup, melted cheese and onion.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix together and put in a buttered baking dish.
Set in pan of hot water, 1-inch deep.
Bake at 350° until firm (about 30 minutes).
Serve hot with Mustard Sauce or cold with Cucumber Sauce.
Serves 6.

title: whole wheat granola muffins
directions: In
mixing
bowl, stir together flours, granola, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg, milk and oil and add all at	once to	dry
ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Fill greased muffin
pans 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix the melted margarine and 1 tablespoon sugar and the crushed pretzels.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put 1 cup chopped pecans and 1 small can coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix per instructions on box.
Pour over the nuts and coconut. Mix 1/2 stick butter (melted), cream cheese (softened) and 1 box powdered sugar.
Drop this mixture by tablespoon on top of cake mixture.
Keep the cream cheese mixture at least 1/2-inch from the edge of pan.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Cool in pan 30 minutes and invert on plate.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix with rotary beater.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until an inserted knife will come out clean.

title: spanakopitta(spinach pie)
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze free of as much water as possible. Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter until a light golden brown. Add scallions and cook until they wilt.
Add spinach and seasonings.
Toss lightly.
Remove from heat and add milk.
Beat eggs lightly in another bowl and add Feta cheese, coarsely crumbled.
Add to spinach mixture; mix well.
With a pastry brush, coat bottom and sides of an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish with melted butter.
Line with 8 sheets phyllo, brushing each sheet with melted butter.
Do not trim overhanging sections.
Pour in spinach mixture and fold overhanging sections back over filling.
Top with 8 sheets of phyllo, brushing each sheet with butter.
Trim overlap.
Brush top with butter and score into squares or diamonds.
Bake in a 350° oven 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: garden supper casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix bread cubes, cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Spread half the mixture in greased 1-quart casserole; top with peas.
Cook and stir onion in 3 tablespoons margarine until onion is tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk; heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in meat.
Pour this over peas. Arrange tomato slices on top and sprinkle with remaining bread mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
May use desired vegetable and/or meat.

title: sun-dried baguettes
directions: Slice bread into 16 slices.
Brush each slice with a mixture of oil and Parmesan cheese.
Slice sun-dried tomatoes and place on top.
Add Mozzarella cheese, basil and green olives.
Place slices on ungreased cookie sheet and bake about 15 minutes in 375° oven.

title: easy 15-minute peanut butter fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugars, salt and milk.
Cook until temperature reaches 240° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat with a wooden spoon several minutes until thick and creamy and gloss disappears.
Spread in a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 48 pieces.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion for 5 minutes in small amount of water (1/4 to 1/2 cup).
Add to the next 6 ingredients.
Melt stick of oleo; put half in mixture and half on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, mushroom soup and 1/2 can onions.
Cook at 325° in a casserole dish in the oven 30 minutes, uncovered.
Pour remaining onions on top and cook until brown, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: vegetable nibbles
directions: Spread refrigerated dough in a 9 x 13-inch pan, keeping dough in one piece.
Bake to package directions.
Cool.
Spread crust with softened cream cheese.
Sprinkle with spices to taste.
Add very finely chopped vegetables.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese. Cover and chill.
To serve, cut into squares.

title: terrace baked beans
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Mix together with all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: plain old fashioned soup
directions: Peel potatoes and onions and dice and boil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil and cook about 5 minutes until hot.
Serve with cornbread.

title: cheese ball 2
directions: Mix dressing, mayonnaise and milk together with electric mixer.
(Divide this mixture in half and freeze for later use if not serving more than 24 people.)
Add cream cheese, then blend Cheddar cheese in by hand.
Place in bowl in freezer for 30 minutes; then shape into ball and roll in pecans.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: sesame chicken on skewers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate in fridge for at least 12 hours.
When ready to serve, heat 3 inches of frying oil in a pan to medium high heat.
Deep fry chicken till done and roll in sesame seeds and skewer.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush your Oreos up until they're very fine.
Make your pudding.
Make a layer of crushed Oreos on bottom of bowl (about 1-inch thick).
Spoon a layer of pudding (1-inch thick) over Oreos.
Continue with a layer of crushed Oreos, then pudding and so on until you reach the top.
Make your top layer crushed Oreos. Then arrange you gummy worms on top.

title: cream of wheat corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients (do not beat).
Bake at 450° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beef tips on noodles
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper and rub into steak.
Cut into desired pieces and brown in bacon grease.
Heat to boiling the remaining ingredients and in a greased baking dish pour this sauce over steak.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Serves 4.

title: oatmeal pies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Place in pie shell and bake for 30 minutes.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: Pour rice in large deep cooking dish, then sprinkle mushrooms and lengthwise cut onion onto rice.
Place chicken pieces.
Season with seasoned salt, garlic salt and pepper on top of onion, mushrooms and rice.
Add 3 cups water.
Cover with tinfoil.
Cut small slits in foil for steam to escape.
Cook 40 to 50 minutes at 425° or until chicken is done and water is evaporated.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream sugar and well beaten eggs.
Mix and sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with milk, then add vanilla (if desired) and bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: easy tamale pie
directions: Brown the meat in the shortening.
Mix with other ingredients. Pour into pan or casserole.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: grape fizz
directions: Half fill 8 glasses with ice.
Pour 1/2 cup grape juice over ice.
Add 1/2 cup ginger ale.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl with a lid.
Add sugar, oil, vinegar, water, salt and pepper.
Marinate overnight.
Pour off marinade after 24 hours.

title: quick pickled peaches
directions: Drain syrup from peaches. Combine syrup with sugar, vinegar, cinnamon and cloves.
Let come to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over peach halves and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: ground beef delight
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Cook noodles as package directs.
In mixing bowl, blend beef, onion, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Blend noodles, cream cheese and sour cream.
Layer into greased baking dish.
Top with the Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey breast casserole
directions: Slice
turkey	breast	 into
1/4-inch
slices.
Layer asparagus, turkey, cheese,	asparagus,
turkey and cheese in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 3/4 hour, until heated through.
Very easy to prepare, and delicious too!

title: scrambled tofu
directions: Rinse tofu
in cold water;
drain and mash with a fork. In a skillet,
saute
onion in a little water until soft.
Add remaining ingredients
and
stir
together well on medium heat five to ten minutes.
Yields 4 servings (2 1/4 cups).

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, eggs and oil in separate bowl.
In another bowl, mix sugar and cinnamon.
Pour half the batter in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle half of the sugar and cinnamon over this. Swirl with a fork or knife.
Add the other half of batter and swirl in remaining cinnamon and sugar.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Glaze.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Dice cheese into microwave safe dish and melt.
Add drained tomatoes smashed into chunks and peppers stir in and microwave for 1-1/2 minutes longer so everything can be mixed easily.
Serve with corn chips to dip or serve by pouring the cheese over a serving dish of corn chips.

title: cinnamon crisp
directions: Tear floured tortillas into small pieces; deep fry for only a few seconds.
Take out of hot oil and roll in cinnamon and regular sugar or powdered sugar.

title: delicious casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery until celery is clear; add meat and cook until meat is done.
Then add corn, spaghetti, Velveeta and chilies.
Serves lots of people, you can double the recipe very easily.

title: cheddar chicken divan
directions: Make a white sauce with the margarine, flour, milk and seasonings.
Add 1 3/4 cups of the cheese.
Stir until melted. Arrange cooked broccoli and chicken in a baking dish.
Top with sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Fry bacon and crumble in small pieces.
Combine hamburger, onion, bacon and all ingredients in small roaster and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: beef with broccoli
directions: Marinate beef in soy sauce and pepper for about 2 hours. Heat oil in pan and stir-fry the marinated beef until tender.
Add broccoli; mix and stir-fry for about 3 minutes.
Transfer to a serving dish and serve hot.

title: marinated garden tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes and onions in a shallow serving bowl.
In another bowl, combine the remaining ingredients; pour over tomatoes.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers into a gallon jar or 4 quart jars, packed tight.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers. Tighten lids and refrigerate.
Ready to eat in 5 days.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cheese blintz
directions: Cut off bread crusts.
Roll flat with rolling pin.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and egg yolks with electric mixer.
Spread mixture on bread.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Cut into thirds.
Roll in melted butter, then cinnamon and sugar.
Freeze on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly browned. Serve with sour cream or applesauce.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and dry ingredients; mix well.
Add oatmeal, raisins and milk.
Bake in a 375° oven for 12 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix shortening, salt and flour. Add water, egg and vinegar. Mix. Makes 2 single crusts.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Beat sugar, margarine, vanilla and egg yolks in large bowl on low speed 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Beat in flour, salt and baking soda alternately with sour cream on low speed.
Beat egg whites in large bowl until stiff.
Fold batter into egg whites; pour into pan.
Bake approximately 80 to 90 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Trim fat from chicken breast and cut into bite-size pieces. Brown chicken in electric skillet.
Add cream of chicken soup. Add cream of mushroom soup and water.
Simmer and stir until smooth.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Mix in thawed frozen broccoli and French onion dip.
Stir in uncooked Minute rice. Bake uncovered in 350° oven approximately 45 minutes.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes and boil 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Sprinkle Season-All liberally on potatoes in casserole dish.
Melt butter (margarine) and add sour cream.
Stir to mix well.
Pour over potatoes, then cover with foil and bake for 20 minutes covered and 15 minutes uncovered at 350°.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix well and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: sunday dinner roast
directions: Season roast with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Dust with flour and brown in roaster in 1 or 2 Tbsp. of hot vegetable oil. Mix onion soup with hot water and pour over roast.
Add beef broth and carrots.
Cover.
I put this in a 300 degree oven before I go to church and let it bake until I get home (approximately 4 to 5 hours).

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat Dream Whip, cream cheese and sugar.
Spread in graham cracker shell.
Top with cherry pie filling; chill.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Bring sugar, celery seed and vinegar to a boil; pour over kraut mixture and marinate overnight.
This keeps one week.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: *Dip banana slices in lemon juice.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Combine chicken with celery, onion and salad dressing.

title: pepperoni tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Drop by teaspoon into greased miniature cupcake tins.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes. Makes 25 to 30 tarts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, mayonnaise, soup, eggs, minced onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Melt butter and combine with stuffing.
Sprinkle on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: miss nanolean's haystacks
directions: Mix morsels on low heat or double boiler.
Add noodles and peanuts.
Stir until coated.
Drop on wax paper and let cool.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Cook celery and onions in small amount of salted water until just tender.
Place a layer of cracker crumbs in bottom of casserole.
Start making layers of ingredients; first spoon in seasoned cream sauce, then celery and onions, dash of red and black pepper and salt to taste.
Add some oysters.
Repeat layers until all layers are used.
Place crumbs on top and dot generously with butter, enough to season through the casserole. Bake at 350° about 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve while hot.
Serves 6.

title: carrot cake
directions: For cake, blend oil, eggs and sugar.
Add dry ingredients, then everything else.
Bake at 350° until done.
Cake will spring back and pull away from sides of pan when done.

title: july 4th salad
directions: Dissolve 2 packages raspberry Jell-O in 4 cups boiling water. Pour into 13 x 9-inch dish; chill until firm.
Scald cream and sugar.
Add unflavored gelatin mixture.
Beat in vanilla and cream cheese.
Stir in nuts and pour over chilled gelatin.
Chill until firm.
Dissolve remaining Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add blueberries and juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Pour over cheese layer and chill until firm.

title: white potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Put all the ingredients in and mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until the knife comes out clean.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and chop chicken.
Cook broccoli; drain well.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with chicken.
Combine all remaining ingredients except crumbs.
Spoon over chicken and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hay stacks
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch chips in microwave. Mix in noodles and nuts until well-coated.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. Refrigerate until set.

title: mashed potatoes with wieners
directions: Preheat oven to 375° to 400°.
Split wieners lengthwise nearly through; spread open.
Place, cut side up, on a greased baking sheet.
Heap mashed potatoes on wieners.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Peel, seed and coarsely chop apples and oranges.
Place all ingredients into saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes or until berries are tender and mixture is thick.
Cool to room temperature, then chill.
Keeps for several days in refrigerator.

title: amazin' raisin apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup fluted tube pan. In large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, mayonnaise, milk, eggs, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and cloves.
With mixer at low speed, beat until blended.
Increase speed to medium and beat 2 minutes.
(Batter will be thick.)
Stir in apples and raisins. Turn into prepared pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 12 servings.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put water in a cup; add vinegar to make 2/3 cup.
Put all in a blender; mix well.
Store in refrigerator.
Shake well before using.

title: oreo cookie dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos in a food processor.
Press in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix pudding, milk, condensed milk and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Let set until firm.
Top with cherries.
Chill well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Use a large casserole dish.
Spray with a nonstick spray.
Cook chicken breasts, cut into bite-sized pieces; put into bottom of casserole dish.
Mix milk with soups and sour cream; put over the top of the chicken.
Melt butter in a frying pan, mixing with it the package of stuffing and about 1/2 cup of chicken broth until mixed thoroughly.
Place it over the soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Easy and good!

title: easy bake cheesecake
directions: Combine sugar, cream cheese, lemon juice, salt and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Blend ingredients together.
Beat eggs into mixture, one at a time.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Chill before serving.
Top with favorite topping.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: In a cup, stir all ingredients together until well blended. Cover and refrigerate.
Makes about 1/2 cup.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Gently boil zucchini for 15 minutes.
Add sugar and boil 6 minutes, stirring often.
Add lemon juice and pineapple.
Boil 6 minutes.
Reduce heat and add Jell-O.
Stir.
Pour in jars and seal.
Refrigerate.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all together, except cheese.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° to 375° until firm in the middle.
Sprinkle cheese and bake 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream brown sugar and margarine.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt butter in large pot.
Add sugar, milk and cocoa.
Boil 1 minute; remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter, vanilla and salt.
Mix until well blended.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and let harden.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburger; warm kidney beans.
Mix ingredients.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: crab ball appetizer
directions: Pick through crab meat to be sure there are no shells.
Steam crab meat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Combine crab meat and onions, cream cheese, crab boil, garlic powder and salt together with a fork. Butter hands and roll all ingredients into one large ball. Refrigerate crab ball overnight.
Before serving, pour Heinz chili sauce over crab ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: caboose stew
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into chunks.
Peel carrots and slice lengthwise.
Slice pepper and onion.
Put all vegetables in a large pot.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Shape ground beef into balls.
Set them on top of the vegetables.
Cook on top of the stove on medium for 45 minutes or until carrots are tender.

title: favorite corn casserole
directions: Saut onions in butter. In a large mixing bowl, mix eggs, Jiffy mix, creamed corn, sour cream and 1 cup cheese. Add onions and butter. Mix well. To this mixture, add sugar to taste. Spray a large shallow baking dish with Pam and pour mixture in. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. It does not take long, usually when cheese on top is melted, it is done. This makes a large casserole.

title: penuche
directions: In heavy medium saucepan over low heat, stir together the sugar, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt until sugar dissolves. Over medium heat, bring to a boil; continue boiling, stirring occasionally, until mixture reaches 238° on a candy thermometer or a little dropped in very cold water forms a soft ball that flattens on removal from water.
Remove from heat; cool to lukewarm (110°). Add vanilla.
Beat until mixture holds its shape when dropped from a spoon and loses its gloss.
This takes considerable beating. Quickly stir in nuts.
Pour at once into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cut when cold.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients until potatoes are done.
Bring to boil the next 5 ingredients and add to potato mixture.
Simmer. When ready to serve, may add 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Stir until melted.
May add diced ham if you like.

title: dried apple pie
directions: Divide the dough into 2 slightly unequal portions. Roll the larger portion into a round 1/8-inch thick and fit it into a 9-inch pie plate. Roll the remaining dough into a round 1/8-inch thick and transfer it to a foil-lined baking sheet. Chill the pastry.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put back in mayonnaise jar and refrigerate.
Serve with any raw vegetables.
It keeps for a long time.

title: peach jam
directions: Boil 15 minutes.
Add 6 ounce box jello.
(Orange goes well with peach or apricot.) Boil an additional minute.
Seal.

title: crunchy candy
directions: Measure ingredients except the sesame seeds into a bowl.
Mix well.
Take a pinch of the mixture and roll it into a ball.
Roll the balls into the sesame seeds.
Chill or enjoy them right away. This recipe makes 5 to 6 large 1-inch balls.

title: 60 minute pan rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine 3 cups flour, sugar, undissolved yeast and salt.
Heat milk, water and butter until very warm (125° to 130°).
Stir into dry ingredients.
Mix in egg and enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth, about 8 minutes.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Beat eggs.
Melt butter in 9 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch casserole dish. Mix other ingredients together and pour in dish. Bake 45 minutes in 375° oven.
Enjoy.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Layer peaches in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spread cake mix, pecans, butter and coconut on top.
Bake at 325°
until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: lemon angel squares
directions: Bake and cool cake according to package.
Pour boiling water on gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate until thickened, but not set.
Add enough cold water to lemonade concentrate to measure 2 cups; stir into gelatin.
Beat until foamy.
Beat whipping cream in chilled bowl until stiff.
Fold into gelatin. Tear cake into 1-inch pieces.
Fold cake pieces into gelatin mixture.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with coconut. Refrigerate at least 4 hours or until firm.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco; add sugar and beat well until mixture is smooth. Add egg yolks and beat. Combine flour and soda and add to creamed mixture with buttermilk. Stir in vanilla. Add coconut and nuts. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into two 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: deluxe chocolate pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter and brown sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop well rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen (2-inch) cookies.

title: quick & easy cookies
directions: You can add nuts, M&M chocolate chips, etc.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mashed bananas.
Add sifted flour, soda and salt. Stir in nuts.
Bake in loaf pan in 300° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat catsup, onion, salt, mustard, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce. Add gelatin and let cool.

title: creamy fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients; mix until blended.
Serve with assorted fresh fruit, or spread on banana nut bread.

title: barbecued chicken pizza
directions: Coat chicken pieces in barbecue sauce.
Spread small amount of barbecue sauce on pizza shell.
Top with 1/2 cheese; add chicken and sliced onions.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° on center rack until cheese melts.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach dry. Stir together all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with Hawaiian bread.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
I prefer to put frosting on rolls while they are still warm.

title: pasta primavera with chicken
directions: Combine lemon juice, oil, garlic, basil and oregano in a medium size bowl.
Add chicken; cover and marinate in refrigerator for about 1/2 hour.
Heat nonstick Dutch oven over medium-high heat until hot.
Add chicken and marinade.
Cook, stirring, until cooked through.
Remove chicken with slotted spoon and set aside.
Add asparagus, yellow pepper and carrot to Dutch oven.
Add half of chicken broth.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add remaining chicken broth as needed to prevent vegetables from sticking.
Add stewed tomatoes and chicken.
Gently heat through.
Toss the vegetable mixture with pasta.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Fry hamburger with spices until brown.
Try to drain some grease off.
Cool.
Add pizza and cheese to hamburger.
Spread on hamburger buns and bake about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fluffy cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar to yeast.
Let stand 15 minutes before adding to roll mixture (mix will foam).
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well. Add salt and 2 cups flour.
Mix in, then add 1 cup boiling water and 2 more cups flour.
Combine, then add yeast mixture and remaining flour.
Dough will be soft, almost soupy.
Place dough in greased bowl.
Cover tightly with foil and place in refrigerator overnight.
Do not knead.
Two hours before baking, cut dough in fourths; roll out and spread with butter, white sugar and cinnamon. Let rise and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Ice if desired.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Toss pineapple and cheese together.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Mix all ingredients together (except crackers & butter).
Pour into greased casserole dish.

title: polish chop suey
directions: Mix together.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and pudding, beating until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour and baking soda mix; well.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour
into
tube	pan
and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix well together the margarine, crumbs, peanut butter and 10x sugar and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the chocolate chips and spread over the top of the mix.
Cool and cut out.

title: one-meal dish
directions: Brown pork chops, salt and pepper and add 1/4 cup water. Place potatoes and carrots on top.
Add 1 small onion.
Bake until done, probably 1 hour.

title: "tally ho" salad dressing
directions: Just place all ingredients in a bottle and shake well.
Keep refrigerated.
Will be good for weeks.

title: easy chocolate candy
directions: In a heavy pot lined with butter, mix together the butter, milk, chocolate and nuts.
Cook until mixture reaches 240°, stirring constantly, then pour mixture into buttered lined bowl. Stir in marshmallow cream.
(Coconut de la quere, optional.)
Pour into butter lined flat pan (9 x 13-inch).
Let set for 4 minutes.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with wafers.
Combine sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Fold in drained fruit.
Pour into cookie lined pie plate.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until set.
Cool, then chill thoroughly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hearty soup
directions: Saute onion, garlic and celery in pan; spray with nonstick cooking spray. Add hamburger meat. Cook until meat is browned. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, then simmer until vegetables are tender. This makes a large amount.

title: rice 'n rye
directions: Place all ingredients into a large, heavy saucepan.
Cover. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and gently boil approximately 45 to 55 minutes or until wild rice and brown rice are tender.
The rye berries will be firm and golden/rust colored.
The three textures and flavors are a delight!

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Mix together the sour cream, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk. Put pieces of angel food cake in a punch bowl or glass bowl.
Add layer of Cool Whip mixture.
Then add layer of strawberries. Repeat layers of angel food cake, Cool Whip and strawberries.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, powder, salt and cinnamon.
In a separate bowl, mix sugar and oil.
Beat the carrots into the sugar and oil mixture and beat in one egg at a time.
Add the dry ingredients and pecans to sugar mixture; beat well.
Pour into a well greased 9x13 pan.

title: beef hash bake
directions: Lightly mix beef, potatoes, onion, parsley, salt, pepper, Worcestershire and milk.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: diet soup
directions: Cover all ingredients with water in a large pan.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
This soup will not add calories so eat all you want.
The more you eat, the more you will lose.
Eat lots of fresh fruits and vegetables.
Try to avoid foods with fat.

title: mary's curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Great as a raw vegetable dip.

title: arkansas doodle cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: red velvet cake(club member: brandi cook)
directions: Cream cheese, sugar and eggs. Sift flour, salt and cocoa.
Add sifted ingredients; alternate with buttermilk, vanilla, vanilla to cream cheese. Beat well. Fold in soda and vinegar mixture. Pour in 9-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: black bean dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender or food processor and blend until smooth.
Simmer until hot.

title: bean burritos
directions: Combine picante sauce and beans, put aside.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish with Pam.
Spoon bean mixture in middle of tortilla, sprinkle with cheese.
Fold tortillas and place seam side down in dish.
Bake in tightly covered dish (I use aluminum foil) for about 15 minutes on 400°.
Serve immediately with toppings.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix flour, sugar and yeast well.
Set aside.
Mix water and oil. Combine the two mixtures.
Bake at 400° to 425° from 12 to 15 minutes in buttered muffin tins.
Dough keeps in the refrigerator for 1 to 2 weeks.

title: fudgey pecan pie
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and cocoa, stirring until well blended. Remove from heat and set aside.
Beat eggs slightly; stir in syrup and salt.
Add cocoa mixture; blend well.
Stir in pecans. Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Cool; let stand 8 hours before serving.
Garnish with whipped topping.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter together.
Add sugars and cream until fluffy.
Add beaten egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together; add to mixture.
Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Press down with floured fork.
Bake in moderate oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into deep pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken or pork
directions: In saucepan saute butter and onion until onion is clear looking, then add other ingredients.
Bring to a rapid boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Makes 1 quart.

title: mom's pie crust
directions: Cut lard into flour with a pastry blender until crumbs form. Sprinkle with salt.
Beat egg well and drizzle on crumbs.
Add vinegar.
Stir with fork.
Drizzle water and stir again with fork until dough comes together to a form a ball.
Roll out on a floured board to desired size.
