This makes enough dough to form 2 double crust pies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple. Combine next 6 ingredients and stir into zucchini mixture.
Add nuts and raisins, mixing well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: open-faced chopped ham
directions: Saute green pepper and onion together, then mix together with other ingredients.
Put 1 tablespoon mixture on half of a bun and toast at 350° until cheese melts.
Mixture will keep in refrigerator indefinitely.

title: summer slush
directions: Mix sugar and water on stove until dissolved, then add juices. Fill 6 ice cube trays.
When frozen, wrap 4 or 5 cubes per drink individual.
Put into glass of ginger ale; chop with fork.

title: delightful ham rolls(appetizer)
directions: Cream the cheese, garlic and mayonnaise.
Add nuts.
Spread mixture thinly on each slice of ham.
Roll like a jelly roll. Chill.
Cut each roll into 1-inch slices.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw broccoli and drain all water.
Mix the oleo, Cheez Whiz, broccoli, eggs, onion and Jiffy cornbread mix.
Pour into a greased skillet or pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until done.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into an iron skillet or baking pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandma smith's molasses cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and mix.
Add molasses and mix.
Add vanilla and mix.
Combine flour and baking soda.
Add to other mixture.
Cookie sheet holds 12 cookies.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: make your own rondele
directions: Blend all ingredients together and chill for several hours before serving.
Makes 1 cup. Serve with vegetables, crackers or chips.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box.
In saucepan, put Cheddar cheese soup, 1 can (soup) evaporated milk and 1 can milk; simmer until thoroughly mixed.
Grate or cut in small pieces the sharp Cheddar cheese and add to soup mixture.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Chop first 7 ingredients.
Put in a large bowl and mix well. Add salt and pepper.
Heat milk and oleo in a saucepan over medium heat until oleo is melted.
Pour over chopped ingredients and mix. Place in a casserole dish and bake at 375°, covered, for 45 minutes and uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In large bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add almond extract.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Butter 13 x 9-inch pan.
Turn mixture into pan. Spoon pie filling into the cake in 16 spots, spacing 4 spoonfuls evenly in each direction.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until cake tests done.
Place bottom side up on serving plate.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: charleston cabbage
directions: Cook until done and drain.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Easy to mix.
Pour all ingredients into large bowl and mix thoroughly until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan and bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 300°.
Cake is finished when toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: california chicken pie
directions: Prepare potatoes, celery, onion and carrots; boil in juice of peas until done.
When nearly done, add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Remove from stove; stir in flour.
Add cold milk all at once.
Return to stove; stir constantly until sauce boils and thickens.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt to sauce.
Remove fluid from tuna in can; rinse with cold water.
Add fish to drained vegetables, adding peas last.
Put in greased casserole; cover with cream sauce.
Bake in a 425° oven for about 25 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.
Serve over patty shells or with rolls.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Mix and spread on English muffins.
Cut in pie shape pieces. Bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Thaw pie shells.
Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add vegetables and saute 5 minutes.
Mix soup, spices and turkey into vegetable mixture.
Pour into pie shell and cover with top crust and press together edges.
Bake 10 minutes in 400° oven.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake an additional 40 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg yolks.
Add condensed milk and lime juice; beat until thick.
Beat 1 egg white until stiff, then fold into the mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: milkshake
directions: Put in blender in the order given.
Blend about 5 seconds. Makes 1 large glass.

title: linda's fudge
directions: Combine milk, chocolate bits and vanilla in a microwave-safe bowl.
Put in microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Stir and make sure it is fairly warm.
If not, put back in for 1 more minute.
Add nuts if you choose.
Put in an 11 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Let set in refrigerator for a couple of hours.

title: raspberry streusel squares
directions: *I prefer seedless preserves, but either is fine.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix moist ingredients.
Combine mixtures.
Bake in paper lined muffin tins 400° for 20 minutes or 2 loaves zucchini bread, 350° 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Mix in vegetables, seasoning, and Italian dressing.
Best if made the night before.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: In a large bowl cream together potatoes and butter.
Slowly add other ingredients.
When well blended bake in a 9-inch pie shell at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and cook 55 minutes.

title: trifle
directions: Break pound cake into small pieces (can spread with fruit jam if desired) and place in bottom of deep glass dish.
Thaw fruit; drain and spoon on top of cake.
Prepare jello according to package directions and pour over fruit and cake.
Refrigerate until set.
Prepare vanilla pudding according to package directions and pour quickly over top of set jello.
The pudding sets up quite fast so you could do this as late as an hour before serving.
Chill.
Just before serving, add whipped cream and decorations.

title: lemon ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in an ice cream freezer 10 to 15 minutes or until ice cream freezer stops turning.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Turn into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serve with sauce.
Serves 8.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Grate the onion. Add the sugar.
Let stand 20 minutes. Add the vinegar, oil, salt, celery seed and dry mustard.
Mix well and store in refrigerator. Shake well before using.
Makes more than 2 cups.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Put shrimp in 9 x 13-inch pan with seasonings. Place pan on grill until shrimp turns reddish-orange.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix flour and cheese. Cut in the shortening. Add milk until a soft dough is formed.
Roll out on a floured board about 1/2-inch thick. Cut with round cutter and bake 10 minutes at 425°.

title: pasta and pork
directions: Boil the package of spaghetti.
Add 1 teaspoon of oil to water to avoid sticking.
While boiling, start dicing veggies.
After dicing veggies, put in saucepan and add water.
Cover and let steam for 15 minutes.
Put pork chops in pan.
Add a teaspoon of oil and salt to taste.
Let simmer for 10 minutes on each side.
Ten minutes into simmer, add veggies to pan over chops with juices from veggies.
Add brown sugar.
Strain spaghetti.
Serve pork chops on side.
Pour sauce with veggies over spaghetti.
Enjoy.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine or butter in large pan, set aside.
Mix all the other ingredients together, then add melted margarine. Pour into a greased baking pan.
Bake 1 hour at 275°.
Cool and cut in squares.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.
Add coconut and spices (1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg), if desired.

title: fat apple chocolate cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 65 minutes at 325° or until tester comes out clean.

title: nellie reed's molasses-blueberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Bake at 350° in greased 8-inch square pan for 60 to 70 minutes or until done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare corn bread according to directions.
Saute the onion in margarine.
Mix onions, chicken, soup and broth together.
Pour over crumbled corn bread.
Mix together well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday mold
directions: In large bowl, cut up cranberry jelly; add Jell-O and 3 cups boiling water.
Mix well.
When Jell-O is dissolved, add 2 cups cold water and juice of lemon.
Peel and seed oranges.
Grind and add pineapple with nuts and dates.
Pour into mold and let stand until firm.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan).
In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until slightly brown.
Cool thoroughly, then cut into squares.
Loosely cover leftovers, if there are any!

title: grandma porolis' enchilada sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and crushed garlic in oil until tender.
Add tomato puree, water, Kitchen Bouquet, oregano, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Let simmer about 20 minutes. Meanwhile, cook tortillas in oil in frypan just to soften.
Drain on paper towel.
Dip in sauce.
Fill with your favorite fillings. Pour remaining sauce over top of prepared enchiladas.
Top with cheese.
Bake for about 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions. Meanwhile, saute crushed cloves of garlic in butter and olive oil. Remove garlic and add melted butter to hot spaghetti. Stir in Parmesan cheese and place mixture in deep baking dish which has been sprayed with vegetable oil. Cover top with Mozzarella or Muenster. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serve with Cucumber-Onion Salad.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, blending well. Stir in applesauce. Mixture will make a stiff dough. Roll out to 1/4 inch thickness on ungreased cookie sheet or wax paper.

Use cookie cutters to get desired shapes. Punch hole with a small pen for the ribbon. Another alternative to the hole is to cut 2 inch lengths of copper wire, make horse shoes and stick them in the top of the ornament. Let dry for several days. Helps to turn them over for Good Luck!

title: black bottom pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, Karo syrup and margarine and stir in pecans and semi-sweet chocolate.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Filling should be less set in center than on the ends.

title: garlic ranch pita triangles
directions: Combine the butter with the Ranch dressing, garlic powder and hot sauce.
Spread 2 tablespoons butter mixture on each of 12 whole pitas. Sprinkle with dill weed and/or sesame seed.
Cut pita into 6 wedges and bake on cookie sheet at 350° until golden brown. Serve with chile or as an appetizer.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cream together sweet potatoes, vanilla, salt, milk, eggs, butter, sugar and cinnamon.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Makes for one baked pie shell.

title: delightful cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage thoroughly (leaving cabbage whole), using circular motion with a knife.
Set aside.
Bring 2 quarts of water to a boil.
Place cabbage in water and blanch, removing leaves as they separate from head.
Place leaves in a shallow dish to drain and cool.
Trim heavy ribs from cabbage leaves.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix well; shape into 20 meatballs.
Cook meatballs on the stove.

title: veggie beef soup
directions: Cook as directed on envelope.
Serves 4.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in boiler.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Turn off and add other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Eat when cool.

title: gone-all-afternoon stew
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Put all ingredients in a large casserole dish with lid.
Mix well.
Cover and bake 5 hours.
No need to brown meat ahead.
Or, put all ingredients in crock-pot for 6 to 8 hours.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Store in airtight container. Use 2 tablespoons per 1 cup serving.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown chops in butter and place in shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and cook and stir until hot and bouillon cube is dissolved.
Pour over chops.
Cover and bake in a preheated 350° oven about 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix syrup, brown sugar and butter together and bring to a boil.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn and mix well.
Put on a greased pan and bake at 200° for about 40 minutes. Store in tightly covered container until ready to eat.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat the cream cheese and Cool Whip until fluffy. Stir in rest of the ingredients and refrigerate.

title: lemon fingers
directions: Mix and pat into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Cut breasts in small strips.
Mix egg whites and milk together.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and lots of black pepper in paper bag.
Dip chicken strips in egg mixture.
Drop in bag and shake until coated. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with nonstick spray.
Repeat steps with remaining strips. Bake at 425° for 40 minutes, turning strips once.

title: busy day casserole(microwave recipe)
directions: Crumble the beef into a 3-quart casserole and cook on full power 4 to 5 minutes or until beef is no longer pink, stirring halfway through cooking time.
Drain beef.
Mix in sauce, water and macaroni.

title: shanghai spareribs
directions: In small bowl, combine sugar, red wine vinegar and ketchup. Set aside.
Heat water to boil. Add ribs and cook 25 minutes. Drain and pat dry with paper towel.
Marinate ribs with rice wine, soy sauce, salt, garlic and pepper.
Toss and stir ribs, marinating 45 minutes. Remove ribs from marinade and pat dry. Coat with cornstarch. Heat 3 cups oil and fry ribs for 3 to 4 minutes. Drain. Re-fry again for 2 minutes.
In skillet heat red wine vinegar mixture.
Add the fried ribs. Toss and stir until hot and well coated with sauce, about 2 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken casserole
directions: Bake chicken and cut into cubes.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix sour cream, soup and seed together.
Pour over chicken.
Melt butter and crush crackers into butter.
Pour over sour cream mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir
together	butter,
sugar	and
milk
in a 3-quart saucepan.
Bring
to
a
boil, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes. Remove
from
heat;
stir in the peanut butter chips (I use Reese's).
Add
the marshmallow cream, vanilla and peanut butter. Mix
good and pour in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk. Add butter.
Cool.
Crumble yeast with 1 tablespoon sugar and mix until liquid, then add to cooled milk. Mix 1/2 cup sugar to eggs.
Add salt.
Combine with milk mixture. Stir in flour.
Cover and let rise in refrigerator overnight. Divide dough into 3 parts.
Roll each part into a circle, about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 16 pie shaped wedges. Roll into crescent rolls and let rise for 4 hours.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes 48 rolls.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain liquid from pineapple and beets. Heat this liquid with lemon juice, vinegar and 1/2 cup water. Dissolve raspberry jello in it. Dissolve 1 envelope unflavored gelatin in 1/4 cold water. Add to mixture. Let cool. Add pineapple, beets and nuts. Place in refrigerator until firm.

title: tate's pepperoni rolls
directions: Grease hands and make rolls the same way as for yeast rolls. Place a piece of pepperoni (about 1 inch) wrapped in 1/2 slice American cheese in the center of each roll and wrap the dough around it, sealing edges.
(Hands dipped in flour make rolling and sealing the dough easier.)
Let rise to double in size and bake the same as yeast rolls (350°).

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, mix together the flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, baking soda, zucchini, raisins and nuts.
In another bowl, beat together the eggs, vanilla and oil (or applesauce).
Pour over flour mixture; stir until thoroughly mixed.
Turn into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: maple teriyaki salmon fillets
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients. Remove 1/2 cup for basting. Cover and refrigerate. Pour remaining marinade into a large, resealable plastic bag. Add salmon. Seal bag and turn to coat. Refrigerate for 1 to 3 hours.

title: hamburger skillet dish
directions: Brown rice slowly in hot fat in a heavy skillet, stirring frequently.
Add ground meat, onion and celery.
Brown well.
Add tomatoes and other ingredients.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender, about 45 minutes.

title: brandy slush
directions: Mix all ingredients in large covered bowl and place in freezer until it is slush.
Place in glass with ice cream scoop and pour either sweet or sour mix over the top.

title: dill pickles
directions: Let cucumbers stand in cold water (slices, if desired).
Bring other ingredients to a boil.
Pack cucumbers cold into pint jar with 1 small blossom of dill, 1 clove garlic and pinch of alum on top.
Pour hot liquid to fill; seal.
Process about 10 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms, cutting off stems.
Dice 1/2 cup mushroom stems.
Saute onion and mushroom stems in butter.
Cook sausage and drain.
In saucepan, cook spinach, then drain.
Mix sauteed onion, mushroom stems, sausage, spinach and cheese.
Stuff mushrooms. Place in shallow greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: upside-down date pudding
directions: Blend dates with 1 cup boiling water.
Let cool.
Blend together the granulated sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar, egg and 2 tablespoons soft butter.
To the sugar mixture, add flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Stir in nuts.
Add cooled date mixture. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, 1 1/2 cups boiling water and 1 tablespoon of butter.
Pour on top of mixture in baking dish. (It will go to the bottom during baking, making the "gooey" bottom.)

title: sour cream coffee loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy. Add eggs 1 at a time; beat until well blended. Fold in sour cream and lemon rind. Gradually fold in flour to creamed mixture, but do not beat. Spoon half the batter into prepared loaf pan. Blend brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Sprinkle half of this over batter. Spoon remaining batter over sugar layer and top with remaining sugar mixture. Pat down gently. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: nut bread
directions: Sift together the first 3 ingredients.
Add and mix the next 2 ingredients.
Beat together eggs and milk; add to the other mixture.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in moderate oven (350° to 375°) in a loaf pan.

title: quick easy fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Add condensed milk. Blend well.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Blend and pour into buttered dish.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: deep fried squash
directions: Cut squash into 1-inch cubes; let boil for 2 minutes.
Rinse with cold water; pour buttermilk over squash and let set for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Shake flour, cornmeal and squash in plastic bag until well coated.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cut beef in 1-inch cubes.
Roll in flour.
Combine pork and beef; cook until brown, stirring constantly.
Add sufficient water to prevent sticking.
Cover; cook until meat is tender.
Add vegetables, cloves and sufficient water to cover.
Season to taste.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Serve with noodles which have been cooked in boiling salted water.
Makes 6 servings.

title: soy grits croquettes
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Add cooked grits, rice and seasoning. Mold into croquettes, dip in beaten egg, then include meal or crumbs.
Place in shallow greased pan, then place in hot oven about 30 minutes or until brown.
Serve with gravy or tomato sauce.
Serves 6.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour in a well oiled pan. Set pan in pan with warm water. Bake at 400° until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: red slush punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with water until dissolved.
Add sugar and both juices.
Stir well and pour into empty cartons.
Freeze 24 hours at least.
Thaw 2 hours and serve.
No ice necessary.
Should be slushy.

title: microwave nut brittle
directions: Combine syrup and sugar in 1 1/2-quart round, glass dish. Stir until well blended.
Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Cook on High for 3 to 5 minutes or until golden brown. Stir in butter and vanilla.
Cook on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Quickly pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: chinese pork chops
directions: Coat chops with flour.
Brown in hot oil. Top meat with carrots and onions.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and cook over low heat, 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 4.

title: ham rolls
directions: Blend 4 ingredients together in mixer. Split rolls (do not break apart). Spread butter mixture on each side of rolls. Place thinly sliced ham on bottom half; add Swiss cheese. Put top half of rolls on cheese. Put stuffed rolls back on foil tray. Cover with tin foil. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cut rolls apart before serving.

title: salada(greek)
directions: Grill peppers and brown on one side.
Cool and slice into small pieces. Cut up tomatoes into small pieces and mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Salada is great on Mexican food.

title: tommys 4 days cake
directions: 1st Day:
Stir sour cream, sugar and coconut well.
Put in refrigerator.

title: perfect pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta according to directions on package, drain. Stem broccoli 3 to 4 minutes.
Rinse in cold water.
Cut zucchini in thin slices, seed tomatoes, cut in 1/2 inch chunks.
Blend remaining ingredients, pour over bowtie pasta, toss to coat. Serve immediately or cover and chill.
Toss again before serving.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Unwrap the caramels and combine with milk in a medium size glass bowl.
Microwave on high for 1 minute.
Stir and if needed, continue to microwave for 15 seconds.
Stir and repeat, if needed until caramels are melted.
Dip each marshmallow into caramel mixture and then coat well with pecans.
It might be necessary to turn the marshmallows from time to time until the caramel sets.

title: four layer torte
directions: Mix as for pie crust and line a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Melt butter; mix in sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in pineapple.
Fold in bread.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm as side dish with ham.

title: chocolate lace cheesecake
directions: Butter a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a large bowl, blend crust ingredients.
Press into bottom and up sides of prepared pan. Refrigerate.

title: broccoli-rice casserole i
directions: Brown margarine,
onion,
celery
seed
and broccoli in skillet. Add rice, Velveeta
cheese,
cream of celery or mushroom soup and broth or water for extra
liquid to skillet.
Cook until rice is done.
Place in greased baking
dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: "beef and bean" supper dish
directions: Brown beef, drain.
Cook until added onion is tender.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer, covered, about 30 minutes or pour into baking dish, cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
An excellent cold night meal.

title: sausage-bean soup
directions: Crumble sausage into a deep 5-quart casserole.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 6 to 7 minutes or until sausage is no longer pink, stirring every 2 minutes.
Drain off drippings.
Stir in water, tomatoes, beans, onion, green pepper, potatoes, salt, garlic salt, thyme and pepper.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap and microwave on High for 45 to 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: grandmother's scotchie cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter.
Add brown sugar; cream well. Blend flour.
(Mixture may be crumbly.)
Press into bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine sugar and corn syrup in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add butterscotch morsels and peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Stir in corn flakes.
Spread over base.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken, reserving some of the stock.
Melt margarine and add flour (do not brown).
Add chicken broth to flour mixture until thickness desired.
Add chicken.
Place 1 crust in pie plate and fill with chicken mixture.
Cover with second crust and slit top.
Bake at 425° until crust is brown.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, longer if hash browns are frozen.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: In bottom of 2-quart Pyrex dish, melt butter.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over melted butter but do not mix.
Pour fruit over top and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Delicious served warm with ice cream.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Make a well in center and pour in ice water and vinegar.
Mix well.

title: full of bologna
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into large casserole or small roaster.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
This is good also if you change the soup flavor.
Just substitute another cream soup.
This is a good dish for potlucks or picnics.

title: sinfully rich brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Line with aluminum foil and spray foil with Pam.
Place both chocolates and butter in top of double boiler.
Stir until melted and smooth. Remove from heat; add salt, vanilla, sugar and eggs and beat well. Stir in flour until mixture is smooth and shiny.
Stir in nuts. Bake 40 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Freeze for one hour, then cut into small squares.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk, mayonnaise and cheese.
Drop by spoonful onto pay sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes.
If desired, brush tops of biscuits with margarine/garlic mixture.

title: gina's veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all the above ingredients except Crackers and margarine. Put in
a casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 30 minutes).
You can double the recipe, but do not double the topping.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Shape into balls.
Brown in vegetable oil.
Yield:
16 to 18 meatballs.
Add to tomato sauce and cook accordingly.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix with gelatin.
Mix until all lumps disappear.
Make a hole in mix; add eggs, crushed berries and water.
Mix until all lumps disappear, then add oil, food coloring and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: baked mustard chicken breasts
directions: Salt and pepper chicken breasts.
Spread with mustard mix and coat with crumb mix.
Bake in a shallow pan at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: buttercreams
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese in bowl until light and fluffy. Add confectioners sugar gradually, beating until smooth after each addition.
Chill and refrigerate.
Shape into balls.
Melt chocolate with butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in paraffin and vanilla.
Dip candy balls into chocolate to coat.
Place in paper bonbon cups.
Yield:
4 1/2 pounds.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake corn bread according to directions.
Cool and break into large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss and chill for 2 hours or longer.

title: chicken pizza
directions: Combine tomato paste, soup, sauce from pizza mix, salt and pepper.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Prepare pizza crust by package directions and put into pizza pans (if you do not have pizza pans, put the pizza crust into three 9-inch pie pans).
Add chicken to sauce, spread evenly on crust and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 30 minutes or until crust is browned. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in the following ingredients:
graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, Eagle Brand milk and pecans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package. Pour half of the batter into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Meanwhile, melt caramels with butter and milk over low heat. Poke holes in baked cake. Pour caramel mixture over top of cake, then sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts. Pour remaining batter over all and bake for 20 to 25 minutes more. Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: sugar-free banana pudding
directions: Cook pudding as directed on the box and cool in the pan.
Add sliced banana to the cooling pudding.
Put a layer of the pudding on the bottom of a bowl and a layer of the vanilla wafers alternately until all of the pudding is used up.
Top with crushed vanilla wafers.

title: coke barbecue chicken
directions: Put the catsup and Coke or Pepsi in electric skillet. Add the chicken pieces. Cover and cook on simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Turn chicken once during cooking.
(You can use regular or diet soda.)

title: cabbage salad
directions: Heat and bring to a boil the oil, sugar, vinegar and seasonings.
Cool and pour over cabbage.
Cover.
Don't stir.
Let stand 1 hour.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter-irish potato candy
directions: Boil potato in jacket.
Peel potato.
Mash and add sugar as needed to make a stiff dough.
Divide into several portions.
Roll out on sugar sprinkled board-thin but not too thin.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll into a roll.
Wrap each roll in cool dampened cloth for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Slice; spread to dry.

title: cold zucchini salad
directions: Combine zucchini, cucumbers and red wine vinegar.
Mix well and refrigerate for 1 hour. After cooling, combine rest of ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate again for 1 hour before serving.

title: tracie's mounds brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix and press first 3 ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next, mix cream cheese and 1 cup coconut with beater.
Add 2 eggs, then slowly add confectioners sugar.
Spread mixture over chocolate mixture.
Top with 1 cup chocolate chips, 1 cup pecans and remaining coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Brownie should be completely cooked but feel slightly soft to touch.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with stuffing.
Put in bottom of dish. Reserve 3/4 cup of stuffing mix to put on top.
Mix all other ingredients and put in dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, cocoa and soda together.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: emerald salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool until slightly set. Combine cucumber and onion; drain well.
Add cottage cheese, mayonnaise and nuts.
Fold into jello.
Turn into 5 cup ring mold and chill until set.

title: crock-pot pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Cut pepperoni in half.
Cut up peppers and onion.
Mix all in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 1 to 2 hours.

title: brandy slush
directions: Mix together and freeze overnight in airtight container. Spoon into glass with 7-Up, Sprite or Mountain Dew.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cornstarch together, blending well.
Add eggs, mixing only until blended and smooth.
Gradually add milk, mixing and keeping bowl scraped down well.
Stir in vanilla and salt.
Sprinkle flaked coconut and pecans in two 10-inch pie crusts.
Pour in chocolate mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: raisin loaf cake
directions: Place raisins, water, sugar, salt, spices and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Let cool to lukewarm.
Stir in baking soda.
Stir until foaming sets.
Stir in sifted flour and turn into a well-greased loaf pan. Bake in heated oven at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool.
Stores good wrapped in foil until needed.
Refrigerate.

title: melting moments
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch and sugar in medium to large bowl. Blend in butter until soft dough forms.
If dough is too soft to handle, cover and chill.
Shape into 3/4 inch
ball, roll in coconut.
Place on ungreased baking sheet 1 1/2 inches apart. Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pasta and walnut fruit salad
directions: Prepare shells according to package directions.
Drain.
Blend yogurt and orange juice concentrate in a small bowl.
Combine shells and remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Add yogurt mixture.
Toss gently to coat.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled thoroughly.
Nutrients per serving:
217 calories, 6 g fat, 1 mg cholesterol and 44 mg sodium.

title: pierogi
directions: Place flour and salt in a large bowl; cut in softened margarine until completely mixed.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix again.
Add water, mixing until soft, pliable dough is formed, adding more flour if needed.
Cover bowl with waxed paper.
Refrigerate dough for 15 minutes.
Pinch off approximately 3-inch pieces of dough.
Roll on floured surface until pieces are very thin (about 1/8 inch thick). Cut with 4-inch cutter.
Fill with desired filling.
Place filling in center of 4-inch circle.
Moisten edge of circle with water. Fold in half-moon shape, sealing edge with fingers.
Press both sides of sealed edge with fork prongs.
(Dough will never break apart regardless how thinly rolled if sealed properly.)

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread into small pieces.
Add all other ingredients.
Add more broth if needed.
Bake in greased pan for one hour at 350°.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease pie plate. Beat all ingredients until smooth. Pour into dish and bake 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool and serve with fresh fruit if desired.

title: meatball casserole
directions: Combine meat, oats, milk, onion, salt and pepper. Mix well and shape into small meatballs. Place into a 2-quart casserole. Combine catsup, vinegar, water and sugar. Pour mixture over top of meatballs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in skillet in hot oil.
Add peppers, carrots and garlic powder.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with soy sauce. Add to pan with pineapple, cashews, mushrooms, juice, vinegar, sugar and ginger. Bring to a full boil.
Meanwhile, prepare rice and serve chicken over rice.

title: goldie's male & female pumpkin bread
directions: Get a can of biscuits out of the refrigerator and put grease on it.
Put biscuits on a pan.
Turn oven on and put pan in oven. Cook until they're done.

title: albert's aged prime rib
directions: Puncture roast with large fork.
Rub roast with dried rosemary. Place in heavy plastic bag.
Mix soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce together.
Add parsley and garlic, chopped.
Pour mixture over roast in bag.
Close bag tightly with seal.
Marinate for 15 days in refrigerator, rotating bag twice daily.
Remove and discard all mixture.
Cover prime rib.
Top with pepper and bay leaves.
Roast in 325° oven for 30 minutes per pound.
Let stand 20 minutes. Carve as desired.
Serves 15 to 25.
Enjoy.

title: wedding cake icing
directions: Cream shortening with powdered sugar, instant milk and cornstarch.
Add egg and mix.
Add water 1 tablespoon at a time. Leave stiff enough to allow flavoring.
Leave very stiff if using for decorations; extra powdered sugar may be added if not stiff enough.
Use large bowl and standard mixer, not hand or portable mixer.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine beans, pepper, onion and celery.
Mix up vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over ingredients.

title: english cookies
directions: Heat the oven to 325°.
Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Beat the egg yolk.
Add the yolk, flour and vanilla to the sugar mixture.
Spread the mixture over a greased cookie sheet. Beat the egg white.
Spread the egg white over the cookie mixture. Sprinkle with the nuts.
Bake for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cut into small rectangles while still warm.

title: original crispix mix
directions: Melt butter in roasting pan.
Add salts, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well coated.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Cream butter, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar together.
Add the egg and vanilla; blend in the dry ingredients.
Shape dough into balls and roll each in granulated sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Top each cookie with a solid milk chocolate candy Kiss, pressing down firmly so cookie cracks around the edge. Return to oven and bake about 3 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Combine dressing ingredients in a screw-top jar.
Shake well. Refrigerate.
Can be made several days in advance.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Core the cabbage; cook for about 10 minutes so leaves will soften.
Mix all ingredients together.
Fill the leaves.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or can cook on top of stove.
Cover the cabbage rolls with water.
I put about 6 tomatoes on top.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and use as a dip with tortilla chips. Great as an appetizer or as a snack for the kids!

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Prepare broccoli and potatoes (peel and dice).
In a large 6-quart pan, add cream of mushroom soup, potatoes, milk and broccoli.
Cook until potatoes and broccoli are done.
Add heavy cream and cheese.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until done and thickened.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: prune conserve
directions: Combine ham, mustard, 1 teaspoon of grated onion and red pepper seasoning in a small bowl.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add eggs, buttermilk, butter and sour cream.
Preheat oven at 375° and bake 25 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
While still hot, butter top.

title: spring onion rings
directions: Slice onions about 1-inch thick.
Separate into rings.
Place in a large bowl of ice water for 5 minutes.
In a large bowl, mix 1 cup flour, baking powder, egg, buttermilk, vegetable oil, paprika and red pepper to form batter.
In deep fryer, heat oil to 350°. Place remaining 1 1/2 cups flour in small bowl.
In small batches, remove rings from water, dredge in remaining flour, then dip in batter.
Place in hot oil.
Fry for 3 to 5 minutes, until golden brown.
Drain onto paper towels.
Repeat process with rest of rings.
Season with salt.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: german supper
directions: Combine all the ingredients in an electric skillet and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes or until well heated.
Stir occasionally. Serve with hot mustard.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugars. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add vanilla. Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Gradually add to creamed mixture. Stir in oats, raisins and pecans. Shape into 1- inch balls. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 8-10 minutes or until golden brown. Do not overbake. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Let sit for a few minutes.
Then fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: ham risotto
directions: Saute onion in butter with garlic.
Add tomatoes, rice, green pepper and ham.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes until rice is tender.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Peel and slice onions 1/4 inch thick.
Let soak in milk to cover for at least an hour.
Make a thin batter of beaten egg, milk and pancake mix.
Dip onions into batter and drop into hot oil.
They brown quickly and must be turned quickly, but only once.
Drain on paper towel.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and let stand until cool.
Blend shortening, sugar and eggs. Add oats and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: low fat creamy cucumbers
directions: Mix the first five ingredients and pour over the last two ingredients.

title: shrimp bacon bites
directions: Mix shrimp and garlic.
Pour chili sauce over mixture.
Cover and refrigerate, stirring occasionally, for several hours.
Cut bacon into halves.
Cook until limp; drain.
Wrap each shrimp in bacon piece; secure with toothpicks.
Broil with tops 2 to 3-inches from heat until bacon is crisp.

title: low calorie dip
directions: Combine all and chill.

title: delray dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Serve with vegetables.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water according to package directions.
Drain.
Melt butter; blend in flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Add milk; cook over low heat until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese, onion, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add macaroni. Pour into a greased 2 quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until browned.
Garnish with bacon. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: rainbow poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour into 2 round pans (8 or 9 1/2-inch).
Bake as directed.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Put cakes back in pans (clean).
Poke with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Pour 1 cup of boiling water over raspberry Jell-O; stir until dissolved.
Repeat with lime.
Pour 1 Jell-O over 1 cake.
Repeat with second Jell-O and second cake. Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and it's ready to serve.
May use light fruit cocktail and Cool Whip.

title: calves liver - venetian style
directions: Crisp bacon slices (microwave if you have one).
Dredge liver in flour, salt and pepper.
Place oil, 3 tablespoons butter, chopped bacon and garlic in skillet.
Add sliced onions and cook until medium brown.
Add liver slices, sage and cook 2 minutes on each side.
Remove liver; add wine, 2 tablespoons butter and parsley to make sauce.
Stir and cook 1 minute longer.
Place onion sauce over the liver and top with crisp bacon slices.

title: fruit pie(makes two 10-inch pies)
directions: Mix pie filling, pineapple, sugar and cornstarch. Cook slowly until mixture thickens.* Add Jell-O. Mix well and let cool. When mixture has set, add bananas and pour into baked pie shells. Put Cool Whip on top. Keep refrigerated.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Sterilize about 7 (1-quart) jars.
Wash and slice cucumbers (4 to 6 spears per cucumber).
Boil water; add salt and alum.
Stir to dissolve, then add vinegar, heating to near boiling, or let strike a boil.
To each quart jar, add 1 split garlic cove, about 4-inch dill stem, 2 dill leaves and 1/2 large dill floweret.
Place cucumber spears in jar without crowding.
Pour hot vinegar solution (at boiling point) over cucumbers, dill and garlic.
Seal.
(Do only one jar at a time, so vinegar solution will be hot.)
Let set at least 2 weeks before eating.

title: strawberry banana dessert
directions: Cut pound cake into 12 slices.
Wash and clean strawberries. Slice.
In bowl combine condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix. Beat well.
Chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream, then strawberries and sliced bananas.
Line sides and bottom of 3 1/2-quart glass serving dish.
Cover and chill for 2 hours. Garnish with nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: meringue shells
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until frothy.
Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff and glossy.
Put brown paper on a baking sheet.
Shape shells with a hollow in middle.
Bake 60 minutes at 275°.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook grits until done, but not thick.
Add Velveeta cheese, stir eggs into milk.
Add to grits with margarine and garlic powder.
Cook until thick, stir constantly.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole, top with grated American cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cook 10 to 15 minutes before serving. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift flour and 3/4 cup sugar.
Beat egg whites and salt until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and flavoring.
Beat until stiff. Add 1 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Fold in flour mixture. Bake in tube pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: watermelon punch
directions: Scoop pulp from melon.
Remove seeds and mash pulp.
Measure 1 gallon of juice and set aside.
Combine sugar and water and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add 1 gallon watermelon juice and chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale, stirring gently.
Yields 5 1/2 quarts.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: Mix together potatoes, 1 cup cheese, soups, onion, sour cream and butter in a large bowl.
Pour mixture into a sprayed 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour, until mixture is bubbly. Carefully remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and paprika.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: gelatina
directions: In a medium bowl, combine 4 cups boiling water and 4 cups cold water.
Add both boxes jello and dissolve completely.
Remove 1/2 cup of this mixture and dissolve unflavored gelatin in it.
Pour back into bowl along with pineapple, strawberries and bananas. Combine all ingredients. Add whipped topping and mix well. Refrigerate until gelatin sets completely.

title: best ever pot roast
directions: Heat a large black iron skillet (Dutch oven) to very hot. Rub salt, pepper and garlic salt on roast. Place in very hot skillet.

title: scalloped mushroom potatoes
directions: Combine the mushroom soup and milk until well blended.
Add 1/2 cup cheese, pimientos, drained mushrooms, salt and Accent. Blend well.
Add the potatoes and mix well.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix eggs and sugar, then add milk and mix very well.
Add rice.
Cook on top of stove until boiling.
Add vanilla.
Put in bowl. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with plastic wrap to keep pudding from getting a crust on top.

title: raw cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Stir everything together.
Add 1 1/2 cups Miracle Whip or Light 'n Lively salad dressing.
Mix.

title: philadelphia cheese pie
directions: Beat sugar, milk and cream cheese.
Fold in coconut, then Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie shell.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes before cutting.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix salad dressing thoroughly and pour on cabbage.
Serves 25.

title: hush puppies
directions: Chop onions small (tops and all).
Mix all ingredients in bowl and let set for 30 minutes.
With oil hot, take spoon and finger and drop balls of mix into deep fryer, fry until golden brown.

title: coconut haystacks
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring often until candy reaches soft ball stage.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream together butter and sugar, then add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, alternating with milk. Mix well.
Add blueberries.
Spoon into muffin pans.
Sprinkle with sugar on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy; add egg and mix well. Add oats, corn flakes, coconut and oil.
Stir all these ingredients well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to butter mixture. Mix well and add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Makes 11 dozen or more.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix food coloring and Nestle Quik to form paste.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add cocoa paste.
Mix flour and salt.
Add buttermilk and flour alternately.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Mix 1 tablespoon vinegar and 1 teaspoon soda and add to cake.
Stir well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use 3 round layer cake pans, which have been greased and floured.
Ice cake.

title: 2 tone brownies
directions: Beat oleo (use Blue Bonnet) until fluffy; add sugar slowly. Beat well.
Add eggs (one at a time), beating well after each egg. Slowly add flour, pecans and vanilla flavoring.
Mix well.
Place 1/2 of batter in well-greased, floured, oblong baking pan.
Add 1 1/2 cups of chocolate frosting to batter in pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes (do not overbake).

title: cousin carmelita's hot orange drink
directions: Mix all ingredients except boiling water well, then store in airtight container (Mason jar, Tupperware, mayonnaise jar).
Use at leisure.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and dressing.
Stir in with all other ingredients.
Let it set for several hours before serving.

title: low fat strawberries and cream
directions: Pour milk into large bowl,
add
pudding into milk, whip with wire whip until dissolved. Let set for 15 minutes.

title: seafood primavera
directions: Combine lemon juice, cornstarch and salt.
Add shrimp and scallops and soak 30 minutes.
In large skillet over high heat, cook mushrooms, carrots and garlic in margarine until tender.
Add seafood and cook until done.
Add pea pods and onions.
Heat through and serve over hot, cooked pasta.

title: chocolate chip fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter a 10-inch Bundt pan. Dust with flour and tap out excess.
On waxed paper sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl with electric mixer at high speed, beat in cocoa until well blended.
Beat in flour mixture alternately with milk until batter is thick and creamy, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Fold in grated chocolate. Spoon into prepared pan, spreading evenly.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when ready to serve.

title: marinated antipasto
directions: Pour dressing over artichoke hearts, pepperoni, tomatoes, olives and peppers.
Marinate, covered, in refrigerator overnight; drain.
Arrange pepperoni, vegetables and cheese on lettuce-covered platter.
Chill until ready to serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple or pear crisp
directions: Peel and slice
fruit into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add egg and mix until crumbly.
Put on top of fruit.
Sprinkle cinnamon over flour mixture and drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour or until fruit is tender and topping is browned.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together 1 cup sugar, eggs, 2 teaspoons vanilla and cream cheese.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into greased spring pan lined with graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a pan.
Combine other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Baste and turn periodically.
Simple, but very tasty.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or you can put chicken on grill.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Drain artichokes and chop finely.
Mix with mayonnaise and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (just until slightly browned).
Serve with crackers.

title: no peek beef stew
directions: Combine and fold all ingredients together in a covered pot or casserole dish.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Do not remove lid during baking time.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Trim fat from pork chops; place in casserole dish.
Mix sauce, ketchup and jelly; pour over chops.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until meat is tender.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: ground beef casserole(with celery soup)
directions: Brown
beef.
Cook onions and pepper in salt water until tender.
Mix
beef,
onions, pepper and rest of the ingredients into
baking
dish with cooked noodles.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: gingerly spiced meatballs
directions: Combine hamburger meat, bread crumbs, milk, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Form into 30 meatballs using a rounded tablespoonful for each.
Brown meatballs in 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil. Drain excess fat.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in 4 cups boiling water with 2 teaspoons salt, 1 teaspoon black pepper and 1 tablespoon oil for 8 minutes.
Drain; rinse with cold water.
Drain.
Add 2 tablespoons margarine.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Break angel food cake into bite-size pieces and put into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix pudding according to package directions.

title: asparagus with cashews
directions: Prepare asparagus spears by trimming ends, rinsing briefly in cold water and peeling any tough stems.

title: broccoli and noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Add broccoli flowerets and peeled, thinly sliced stems for last 5 minutes of cooking.
Drain noodles and broccoli.

title: granola
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients very well.
Mix oil, water and honey well and add to dry ingredients.
Lay thinly on a cookie sheet and turn every 1/2 hour.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Store in an airtight container.

title: ginger beef
directions: Note:
Chicken broth may be used instead of water.

title: chili
directions: Broil ground beef until brown.
Mix beans and sauce in separate pan, then add meat.
Bring to a boil.
Add chili powder and seasoning pack.
Simmer 10 minutes, then serve hot.

title: lemon jello whip
directions: Add 1 cup of boiling water to jello; dissolve, then add 1 cup cold water.
Let jello almost set, then whip.
Add whipped cream, marshmallows and pineapple.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: stuffed zucchini boat
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cut off stem end of zucchini.
Cut each in half lengthwise and scoop out pulp and seeds (reserve pulp), leaving 1/4 inch shell.
Brown ground beef, onion, garlic and oregano.
Drain fat.
Add chopped zucchini pulp, Parmesan cheese, 1/4 of soup, salt and pepper.
Arrange zucchini shells in 9 X 13 pan.
Spoon mixture into shells.
Spoon remaining soup over top. Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered with foil, at 375° for 30 minutes or until zucchini is tender. Sprinkle grated Mozzarella cheese over boats.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line casserole with 6 slices buttered day old bread.
Layer half of onions, bell pepper, ham or sausage, mushrooms, tomatoes and cheese.
Next layer 6 slices of buttered day old bread and remaining ingredients in the same order.
Lastly, pour beaten eggs over casserole.
Let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Recipe can be halved into 2 small casseroles.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together.
Pour on top of your favorite meat and mmmmm good.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Simmer until melted.
Add meatballs and simmer over low heat for approximately 1/2 hour (crock-pot works well).

title: hawaiian slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Mix mayonnaise, pineapple juice and celery seed together.
Add cabbage and pineapple bits.
Mix well. Refrigerate for at least 4 hours before using.

title: bonbons
directions: Knead first 3 ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Add fruits and nuts if desired.
Place in pre-lined mold and cap.

title: country fried shrimp
directions: Prepare shrimp.
Season with salt and pepper.
In medium bowl add 1 cup of flour and enough water to mix without being too thick or too thin.
Then add shrimp; mix well.
Dip 1 or 2 at a time into deep fryer.
Brown on both sides.

title: ladies cabbage
directions: Starting with pointed end of cabbage quarters, cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Cook until tender with 1/2 teaspoon of salt; drain well.
Add margarine.
Combine cream, cornstarch, sugar, salt and pepper in a small saucepan.
Bring just to boiling, stirring constantly.
Pour over hot cabbage and serve hot.

title: sugar snap peas and peppers(6 servings)
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat. Add veggies and saute for 5 minutes. Sprinkle with soy sauce and lemon juice. Add pepper and salt to taste.

title: praline brownies
directions: Mix chewy fudge or cake-like brownies as directed, except do not add nuts.
Spread in greased 8 to 9-inch square pan.
Combine melted butter, brown sugar and pecans; sprinkle evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan; line bottom of pan with wax paper. Melt chocolate over hot water.
Cool.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend butter to soften in a mixing bowl.
Add sugar. Add dry ingredients, milk and vanilla.
Mix to dampen flour.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs and egg yolk and chocolate. Beat 1 minute longer.
Pour into pan and bake at 250° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: lemon-cheese salad
directions: Combine gelatin with boiling water.
Drain pineapple, measure juice and add water to make 1 cup; then add to gelatin.
Chill until partially set.
Soften cream cheese and add mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Add to gelatin and stir well.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: creamy cherry salad
directions: Chill Eagle Brand milk for several hours.
Drain pineapple. Beat Eagle Brand milk with electric mixer for 15 minutes.
Fold in thawed Cool Whip.
Add pie filling and pineapple.
Enjoy!

title: low-fat brownies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add low-fat spread and applesauce. In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Add vanilla.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in preheated 350° oven in pan sprayed with pam.

title: overnite macaroni and cheese with chipped beef
directions: Put in buttered dish.
Mix ingredients and let stand overnite in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape and put into loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Boil broth, celery, carrots and onion until tender.
Mix together flour and melted butter.
Stir into broth and cook until thick.
Add beer, cheese, salt and pepper.
Simmer and stir until cheese has melted.
Serve with croutons.

title: my favorite chocolate cake
directions: In
a
large bowl, add all ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Mix
on
low speed until moistened, then beat 2 minutes at medium
speed.
Batter
is
quite
thick.
Stir
in chips by hand. Pour
batter
into a Bundt pan that has been greased and dusted with cocoa and bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma's brussels sprouts and nuts
directions: Trim Brussels sprouts of outer leaves.
In saucepan, bring water to boil.
Add sprouts.
Simmer on low until tender.
Melt butter, simmering with nuts.
Add sprouts.
Toss and serve.

title: stuffed vegetables
directions: Quantities depend on the number and size of vegetables to be stuffed.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Mix in next two.
Mix in flour. Roll into balls.
Flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: poor man's fruit cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° in a floured angel food cake pan or Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: chicken burritos
directions: In bowl, whisk together the mayonnaise, picante sauce and salt, mixing well.
In separate bowl, mix chicken, onion, celery, cheese and olives.
Fold into sauce mixture, mixing well.
Spoon chicken mixture into tortillas; fold into burritos.
Microwave each burrito for 45 seconds on High or until hot.
Yields 8 burritos.
Serve with more picante sauce, olives and sour cream.

title: prune bread
directions: Mix alternately the dry ingredients with liquids.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 large or 3 small loaves.

title: wine cake
directions: Add all ingredients and beat approximately 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: jello cake
directions: Make an 11 x 13-inch pan of any white or yellow cake mix according to package.
While cake is hot, use a toothpick to poke a lot of holes in the cake.

title: apple crunch
directions: Cook apples in enough water to cover, and boil low until all water is absorbed.
Add sugar to the apples and spread them into the baking dish.
Sprinkle the cake mix (dry) over apples.
Melt margarine and pour over apples and cake mix.
Sprinkle with nuts and bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Top with ice cream or Cool Whip!

title: chess cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients, except nuts; spread in bottom of a well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: In mixing bowl, combine butter, cheese, sausage and seasonings.
Mix in flour.
Shape dough into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Mix milk, vanilla and pudding.
Add this to first mixture.
Put 1/2 bag of the cookies in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add pudding mix and put remaining cookies on top.

title: mom's brown sugar cookies (drop cookies)
directions: Cream shortening
and
brown sugar together.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add	coffee and water.
Sift together baking powder and flour, add	to other mixture, add vanilla; mix well.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Braise ground beef and onion until done.
Add chili powder, kidney beans, tomatoes (chopped), tomato soup and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer about 15 to 20 minutes.
(Add tomato paste instead of tomato soup for richer chili sauce.)

title: noel tortoni
directions: Cut ice cream into large chunks and place in a well-chilled bowl.
Stir quickly until smooth.
Stir in almonds, cherries, extracts and nutmeg.
Fold in candies.
Spoon into 2 1/2-inch fluted paper or foil baking cups in muffin pan.
Freeze.
Serve plain or top each serving with a dollop of whipped cream and a few additional candies.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large container; mix well. Store in tightly covered container.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour, mustard and soup.
Cook until thick.
Drain vegetables.
In a 2-quart casserole, layer asparagus, peas and eggs.
Pour sauce over this.
Saute 2 tablespoons margarine and bread crumbs to light brown.
Place on top of casserole and sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, except boiling water.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer.
Stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour into two greased 9-inch or three 8-inch pans or one 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes on rack.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Frost.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix grated Cheddar cheese and cream cheese together.
Add chopped onions, chopped olives and Worcestershire sauce.
Chop beef jerky in the food processor; mix with other ingredients.
Add garlic and mix well.

title: corned beef barbecue
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Add barbecue sauce.
Cook onion with 2 to 3 tablespoons oil.
Add to mixture.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts (or any kind you prefer).
Let set in refrigerator 4 hours or longer.
Serves 12.

title: cranberry stuffed squash
directions: Split acorn squash in half.
Scoop out seeds.
In the center put 1 teaspoon margarine, 1/2 tablespoon brown sugar and 1/2 of the whole cranberries.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Repeat to other 1/2 of squash.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or when squash is tender.
May also be done in microwave (times vary on all microwaves).
Great for Thanksgiving and Christmas dinners.

title: maple coconut bars
directions: In mixer bowl, beat butter or margarine at medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add sugar and beat until combined.
Add eggs and maple flavoring; beat at low speed just until combined.
Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture and mix until blended.
Stir in finely chopped coconut and the nuts. Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine pasta, chicken, cucumbers, celery, peppers and onions.
In a small bowl, combine dressing, seasonings, mayonnaise and mustard.
Add to salad mixture; toss to coat.
Cover and chill.
Toss gently before serving.

title: diabetic pineapple meringue pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, salt and pineapple; mix well.
Add lemon juice and margarine or butter.
Beat egg yolks.
Combine in mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Let cool.
Add 12 packs Equal, then pour into pie shell.

title: new mexico hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream, green chilies, onions and peppers. Spread on tortillas and roll up. Place in the refrigerator for 2 to 4 hours or overnight. Slice and serve.

title: homemade irish cream
directions: Using electric mixer, mix all ingredients except whipping cream; mix in whipping cream last.

title: auntie carol's chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken pieces.
Put a layer of rice at the bottom of a casserole pan, then a layer of chicken, then a layer of salsa, then a layer of cheese.
Repeat one more time.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: melodi corr's cinnamon ornaments
directions: Combine spices, mixing well.
Stir in applesauce; mix well. Dust cutting board with cinnamon.
Roll out like cookie dough, about 3/8-inch thick.
Using cookie cutter, cut into desired shapes.
Make a hole in the top of each ornament with a straw or toothpick for hanging.
Let dry on a flat surface for about 1 week, turning every 12 hours.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 spaghetti sauce mix over raw hamburger.
Spread cottage cheese over meat, next the uncooked noodles.
Sprinkle rest of mix over noodles.
Pour juice over all.
Simmer until noodles are done, then cover with cheese and let melt.

title: turkey stuffed peppers
directions: Mix together turkey, egg, rice, salt, pepper, garlic powder and enough corn flake crumbs to bind.
Stuff into cleaned peppers with tops cut off.
Place in 4 1/2-quart pot.
Pour tomatoes over peppers.
Add small amount of water.
Cook 2 hours on low heat, pouring sauce over peppers.
Make meatballs with leftover turkey mixture and cook in pot with peppers.

title: deer roast
directions: Thaw roast completely, then soak in big bowl of water with vinegar or lemon juice.
Soak for 10 minutes.
Rinse well and drain.
Next, coat roast with flour, salt and pepper as you would fried chicken.
Brown in half margarine and oil until golden brown.
Pour water over roast and cook until tender.
After roast is cooked tender, place on baking pan and put sausage seasoning over roast.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Pour catsup or tomato sauce on top.
Put back in oven for another 5 or 10 minutes.

title: party orange soda
directions: In a small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until soft peaks form; beating on high speed, gradually sprinkle in 1/4 cup of sugar.
Beat until sugar is dissolved.
Whites should stand in stiff peaks.
Set beaten whites aside.
In chilled punch bowl, carefully stir orange juice, milk, lemon-lime soda, 1/4 cup of sugar and ground nutmeg until well mixed.
Stir in beaten egg whites.
Serve immediately in punch cups or small glasses.
Makes 8 cups or sixteen 1/2-cup servings.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw the bread and spread it out.
Separate eggs.
Beat the yolks and spread out on the bread.
Sprinkle on the oregano, Romano cheese, salts and pepper.
Add any of the options you wish to. Roll it up into a log; frost the top with the egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly, shape into a loaf and place in a 1 1/2 quart loaf pan.
Put in 350° preheated oven and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Mix and chill.
Garnish with crisp cooked, crumbled bacon just before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Butter casserole pan.
Slice potatoes thin, and alternately layer in pan with green pepper and onion.
Dot with butter; salt and pepper.

title: sour cream, oatmeal, chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and mix well. Alternately add the sour cream and dry ingredients and mix well. Add oatmeal and mix.
Add chocolate chips; fold in with spoon or spatula.
Chill mixture.
Drop by tablespoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Blend graham crackers, melted butter and 2 tablespoons sugar and pat firmly in bottom of buttered spring-form pan.
Mix cream cheese until creamy.
Add 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat until creamy.
Fold slowly into cheese mixture.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until cake is brown.
Take out.

title: dorito pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat and diced onion in frying pan; season with salt and pepper to taste.
Chop Ro-Tel tomatoes and mix with soup; heat until hot.
Mix soup and hamburger meat.
Crumble Doritos in bottom of casserole dish.
Place about half of meat over this.
Grate and sprinkle cheese and crumbled Doritos over the meat.
Add the rest of the hamburger meat.
Top with crumbled Doritos and grated cheese.
Place in oven at 350° until cheese melts; remove and serve.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring water and cornstarch to a boil.
Add jello and Sweet 'N Low.
Cut strawberries in pie shell.
When jello mixture cools, pour over strawberries and cover with Cool Whip.

title: apple empanadas
directions: Make Apple Empanadas by filling flour tortillas with a mixture of apple pie filling, melted butter and cinnamon.
Fold and secure with toothpicks.
Deep fry and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.

title: creeping crust cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 10-inch baking pan.
Mix together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk.
Spoon over melted butter. Mix fruit and sugar.
Pour over dough.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes until crust is golden brown.
(Crust will rise to the top.)

title: marzetti
directions: Brown meat in shortening.
Add onion, green pepper, mushrooms and seasonings.
Cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Combine tomato soup, tomato paste and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook broad noodles in boiling water until almost tender; drain.

title: georgia peach cobbler
directions: Mix 1 cup of the sugar with peaches.
Melt the oleo in glass baking dish in microwave.
Mix together remaining sugar, flour and milk.
Pour this into center of dish containing oleo.
Do not stir.
Next, pour in the sliced peaches.
Put generous amount of sugar on top and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beanstroni soup
directions: In saucepan, brown ham and onion in butter.
Stir in bean with bacon soup.
Blend in water.
Add minestrone soup.
Heat; stir often.
Makes 5 cups.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Depod mushrooms and clean.
Saute pods in butter.
Mix other ingredients together and stuff pods.
Place pods in pan and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in oven at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, top with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Heat at 425° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with vegetable chips or crackers.

title: eggplant dip
directions: Bake whole eggplants in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool.
Cut in halves.
Scoop out pulp; set aside.
Put onion and garlic in bowl or food processor and mince.
Add eggplant and remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve on crackers or as a dip.

title: dilled okra
directions: Wash and drain okra.
Prick each pod with fine pointed knife to allow solution to enter pod.
Pack okra into jars.
Place a small bunch of dill in each jar.
Boil water, vinegar and salt. Fill jars with boiling brine to 1/2 inch of top.
Cap and process in water bath for 5 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread dough on pizza pan; bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: dorothy lamb's peanut butter pie
directions: In small bowl with fork, combine confectioners sugar and peanut butter.
Set aside.
In 2-quart saucepan, stir together 1/2 cup granulated sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt.
Separate eggs.
Warm whites to room temperature.
Add yolks to sugar mixture in saucepan with milk.
Stir with wire whisk over medium heat; stir constantly. Heat milk mixture to boiling.
Cook 2 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions (makes 4 cups).
Fry bacon crisp.
Cut in pieces.
Saute onions and mushrooms in butter. Dilute soup with cream.
Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: fruit cocktail pudding
directions: Sift sugar, soda, salt, flour and egg.
Blend well.
Pour into a greased dish.
Place brown sugar over ingredients; add nut meats.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: white buttermilk cake
directions: Beat sugar and shortening.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes in long pan, 30 minutes in layer pans.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and frozen vegetables. Bring to a boil, then add potatoes. Cover and cook until potatoes are done, about 30 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cabbage soup
directions: In a large stockpot, brown and drain the hamburg, onion and garlic.
Add the can of diced tomatoes and about 4 cups water.
Add beef bouillon to taste, along with the pepper.
Salt to taste.
To the broth, add the cabbage and carrots.
Simmer until the vegetables are cooked.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush cookies with rolling pin.
Spread half of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat slightly.
Mix milk and pudding; let set up. Then mix cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Fold mixture, Cool Whip and pudding together.
Pour over crumbs.
Top with remaining half of cookie crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: rice dish
directions: Use long grain white rice.
Mix all together and place in baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer, if necessary.

title: orange pecan squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and brown sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add 2 cups of flour, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add pecans and mix to blend.
Press evenly over well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake until lightly browned at edges, about 20 minutes.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Gradually add granulated sugar until thick and well blended.
Add orange juice, orange rind, remaining 1/3 cup flour and baking powder; mix to blend.
Pour orange mixture over baked crust and return to oven and bake until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: fruit cake
directions: Boil the raisins for 15 minutes in 2 cups water.
Remove from stove and put a cup of cold water on them.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chickpea and pasta soup(serves 4)
directions: In large saucepan, melt the butter or margarine and cook the onion with the thyme, stirring for 5 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, their juice and the garlic; simmer the mixture, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes.
Add the broth and chickpeas. Simmer the soup, stirring occasionally, for another 15 minutes. Add the pasta and pepper.
Cook the soup until the pasta is warm. Thin the soup with additional stock or water, if necessary.
Serve the soup with a tablespoon of Parmesan sprinkled in each bowl.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add other ingredients and cook on low heat 45 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a heavy aluminum saucepan.
Add colored water.
Cook 3 minutes or until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Cool and knead.
Place in airtight container when not in use.

title: thank you casserole
directions: Slice potatoes into buttered casserole.
Cover with meat. Add undiluted soups and onion.
Crumble potato chips on top. Cover with foil.

title: quesidillas
directions: Put tortillas on paper plate.
Sprinkle handful of each kind of cheese on tortilla.
Place second tortilla on top of cheese. Place in microwave on High for 30 seconds (or may place on cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 2 to 3 minutes).
When cheese melts, remove from microwave or oven.
Cut into triangles.
Serve warm with sour cream or taco sauce.

title: strawberry cake dessert
directions: Bake cake by directions.
Put in freezer for one hour.
Take out and cut down the middle making two layers.
Mix together Cool Whip, sugar, strawberries, and sour cream.
Put on top of one layer and cover with second layer.
Top with remaining mixture.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine dressing, milk, onion, celery, pickle and sauce; pour over lettuce, shrimp and cut up eggs.

title: strawberry-banana salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water in bowl.
Add strawberries. Stir until strawberries are thawed.
Mix in pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour half the mixture into mold. Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream over congealed gelatin. Spoon remaining gelatin over sour cream.
Chill until set. Unmold on serving plate.
Yields 9 to 12 servings.

title: curried rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package instructions.
Cool and fluff rice with a fork.
Mix onion, vinegar, salad oil, curry powder and salt.
Add to cooled rice and refrigerate at least 3 hours. Combine remaining ingredients with rice before serving.

title: rolled oats cookies
directions: Chill mixture.
Roll into balls then roll in powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: aunt myrtle's rhubarb pie
directions: Line large pie plate with pastry.
Sprinkle brown sugar over bottom of pastry.
Fill crust with rhubarb.
Sprinkle granulated sugar, flour or Minute tapioca and cinnamon over rhubarb.
Beat eggs and add milk; pour over rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chinese cole slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage and onions.
Cover and refrigerate.
Break Ramen noodles into small pieces.
Combine noodles, sesame seed and almonds in medium bowl.
Set aside.

title: cranberries with almond relish
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil; continue to boil for 5 minutes. Add cranberries and cook until skins burst, approximately 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and add marmalade and lemon juice. Cool and stir in almonds and Amaretto.
Chill before serving.

title: napoleon cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk and let stand 5 minutes.
Blend with Cool Whip.
Layer in order:
pudding, graham crackers (whole blocks), pudding, graham crackers and top with chocolate frosting (any variety).
