title: four bean salad(east, fast and good!)
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients until sugar is dissolved. Pour above mixture over the beans.
Stir all together gently, but thoroughly.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.
Stores well for up to 1 week.

title: fried cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers and roll in flour mixture evenly.
Put in 2 tablespoons hot grease, turning often until brown and cucumber slices are tender.

title: banana pudding
directions: Reserve 1 banana and 10 to 15 wafers to garnish.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grate cheese.
Let cheese and butter stand at room temperature until soft, then beat with electric mixer. Add salt and red pepper.
Add flour, one cup at a time, until mixture is stiff.
Roll out on wax paper. Cut with small cutter and place a pecan on top of each. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes. Biscuits will be yellow instead of brown.

title: macaroni dinner
directions: Saute onion and celery until almost clear.
Add vegeburger, garlic and pepper.
When celery is cooked, add spaghetti sauce and Cheddar cheese.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or serve immediately.

title: reggie's barbecue spareribs(oven style)
directions: Arrange ribs in a large pan in 1 layer.
Roast in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Meanwhile, in a 1-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat grapefruit juice and remaining ingredients to boiling. Cook 1 minute; stir constantly.
During last 30 minutes of roasting time, brush ribs frequently with grapefruit mixture. Bake until tender.
Over the ribs, use Reggie's barbecue sauce.

title: baked macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Cook macaroni following package directions.
In a large skillet, saute onion in butter.
Add tomatoes, parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Simmer uncovered 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in contents of cheese packet.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese slices and return to oven for 5 minutes to melt cheese.

title: exquisite pie
directions: Soften margarine; mix with sugar.
Add beaten eggs to sugar mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well; pour into pie shell. Place unbaked pie on a cookie sheet and bake in
a preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: *hollandaise sauce
directions: Beat eggs until very thick.
Slowly add lemon juice, then seasonings and then butter, beating after each addition.
Beat thoroughly.
Can be kept in the refrigerator and used as desired. Warm to room temperature before using so as not to cool off food on which you are using it.

title: honey cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 325° until lightly brown.

title: vegetable and bean soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium, cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes, or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: kraut and frankfurters
directions: Brown frankfurters in butter.
Add sauerkraut and onion.
Heat thoroughly.
Add noodles and mix.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients and store in an airtight container.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of hot water.

title: scandinavian almond bars
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter until softened.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and almond extract.
Add flour mixture.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan or dish.
Pour hash brown potatoes into this casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and blend well.
Spoon mixture over potatoes.
Melt butter and add corn bread stuffing mix.
Blend well.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 10 servings.

title: bebida resfrescante fresa y pla tano(refreshing drink of strawberry and banana)
directions: Mix Kool Aid, sugar, water and banana in blender until creamy. Add crushed ice and blend.
Serves 4.

title: hot chinese salad
directions: Slice meat into thin slices and coat with cornstarch. Brown quickly in oil. Add garlic powder. Next, add mushrooms and water chestnuts or bamboo shoots. Cover and heat thoroughly (about 5 minutes on medium heat), stirring frequently. Add remainder of vegetables and cover. Heat for 3 minutes, then stir and cover again for about 2 minutes. Serve over chow mein noodles or rice (with sweet and sour sauce and Chinese mustard).

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan, put rice on bottom.
Mix soup, milk, mayonnaise, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Pour 1/2 soup mixture over rice and stir.
Place chicken on rice, then broccoli.
Pour remaining soup on.
Add cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza dough
directions: Sprinkle yeast over water and stir until dissolved.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar and salt.
Add egg and 1 tablespoon oil. Stir until smooth and glossy.
Stir in 2 cups flour.
On lightly floured board, knead until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes). Place in greased bowl and let rise for about 1 hour.
Punch down and divide in half.
Makes dough for 2 pizzas.

title: bread pudding
directions: Butter bread and cut in 1 inch squares.
Place in lightly greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Slightly beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla and salt and mix well.
Heat milk; slowly add to egg mixture.
Mix well and pour over bread squares.
Stir in raisins and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and add Marshmallow Creme.
Blend until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: super salad
directions: Heat jello, sugar and pineapple over low heat until jello is dissolved.
Cool.
Add buttermilk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: christmas coffee cake
directions: Combine biscuit mix, sugar, mincemeat, egg, milk and melted butter; beat vigorously 1/2 minute.
Bake in greased 6 1/2-cup ring mold at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
Invert on platter, drizzle with orange icing.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Serve warm.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Remove.
Stir.
Cook 3 1/2 minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla; stir.
Cook 2 minutes; remove.
Add soda and mix quickly, then pour on greased cookie sheet.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until meat falls off the bone.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of broth.
Layer breasts in 9 x 13-inch dish or pan. Combine chicken and celery soups and milk.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle dressing mix over the chicken mixture.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease casserole dish.
Mix crabmeat, cream cheese, sour cream, mayo and 1 cup of Cheddar cheese.
Pour mixture into greased casserole dish and spread 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese on top.
Cook for 40 minutes.
Serve with B J. flats crackers.
Enjoy!

title: pecan-apple pie
directions: While preparing crust, mix 1/2 cup of the pecans into the dough.
Separate the egg and beat the white with 1 tablespoon of water.
Brush this glaze onto the two pie crusts, then refrigerate them until ready to fill.
Peel and slice apples thin and place them in a bowl with the brown sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and the remaining pecans less one tablespoon.
Put all into bottom pie shell and brush edges with egg glaze.
Dot with margarine, then place top crust on pie and brush it with the glaze and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 425°, then reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake until golden brown (about 40 minutes).

title: banana punch
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Mix with orange juice, lemonade and pineapple juice.
Add bananas and freeze.
When frozen, remove from freezer and mash with a potato masher.
Add ginger ale. Serve semi-frozen.
This is very good.

title: mother's brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together, roll out, cut and bake at 350°.

title: super-easy fruit cobbler
directions: Use 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt margarine in pan; set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, milk and salt.
Pour this batter over melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Pour fruit, including juice, over batter.
Once again, do not stir.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13 pan. Spread coconut and pecans in bottom of pan. Mix cake according to directions. Pour over coconut and pecans. Melt margarine. Add cream cheese and powdered sugar. Mix well. Spread over cake. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done. Test with toothpick. Cake will fall and crack, giving an earthquake appearance.

title: buttermilk cheese bread
directions: This is a good bread for holiday meals.
The recipe fits a 1 1/2 pound bread machine.
Make sure all ingredients are at room temperature.
This recipe can also be handmade by using 2 loaf pans.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet.
Drain fat off of beef. Add onion, Mrs. Dash and garlic salt.
Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Drain; mix with meat and onion.
Add stewed tomatoes, corn, kidney beans and tomato sauce; simmer for 5 to 10 minutes on low heat.

title: beef stuffed bell pepper halves
directions: Cut the peppers in half lengthwise.
Discard seeds and stems. Arrange, cut side up, in baking pan about 9 x 13-inch.
Sprinkle the salt in a frying pan.
Place over medium heat.
Add the beef, onion, garlic, cumin, oregano and chili powder.
Cook, stirring frequently, until crumbly, about 5 minutes.

title: upshaw pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Fill empty sugar box with flour to measure 1 pound.
Sift flour 3 times.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternately with flour, adding a little pineapple juice to mix. Continue until eggs, flour and juice are used.
Mix thoroughly with electric beater.
Bake in tube pan, greased and floured, for 1 hour at 325° until done.

title: artichoke rice dill salad
directions: Boil broth.
Add rice and cook 20 minutes or until tender. Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: irish strawberry dessert loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans (9 x 5-inch).
In medium bowl, stir thawed strawberries, eggs and oil. In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and nuts.
Add strawberry mixture and stir until blended well. Pour into pans.
Bake 1 hour.

title: american chow mein
directions: Add celery, onions, soy sauce and sugar to ground beef; simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Transfer to large pan and add bean sprouts, mushrooms, water chestnuts and water.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Thicken with flour or cornstarch.
Serve over rice and Chinese noodles. Add more soy sauce to taste while cooking.

title: old fred
directions: Take one whole chicken, cut back bone and spread chicken out. Separate skin from top (stomach).
This is to be stuffed.

title: moist corn bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13
1/2-inch
cake
pan.
Bake
in a 350° preheated oven. Reduce heat to 300°.
Bake approximately 1 hour.

title: cheese dish
directions: Pour milk over bread crumbs.
Beat eggs.
Grease a small casserole.
Combine
all ingredients except paprika.
Pour into casserole; dust with
paprika.
Bake
in oven at 350° about 1/2 hour.

title: french toast a l'orange
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add orange juice, orange liqueur, milk, vanilla, salt and orange rind; mix well.
Dip bread in mixture, turning to coat all surfaces.
Place single layer in baking dish.
Pour remaining mixture over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with jackets on.
Season with salt and pepper. Fry the bacon; pour off half the grease.
Mix the water, vinegar and sugar in a small bowl; bring it to a boil.
Thicken with the bacon fat and flour mixed to gravy thickness.
Pour over potatoes and bacon.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 325°.

title: easy rotel chili(hot!)
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet until well done.
Rinse well with hot water.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients in pan.
Heat until it boils, turn down to simmer.
Cook for 15 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: With the pineapple juice blend vanilla pudding and Tang.
Stir in fruit mixture.
May add bananas or coconut.
Chill and serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs together with mixer.
Add apples. Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to cream mixture.
Can add nuts, if desired (1/2 cup).
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Add any kind of salad dressing you like.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Put together eggs, sugars, butter, pumpkin pie filling, vanilla and milk.
Mix well; add flour, soda and pumpkin pie spice.
Mix well.

title: virginia's lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.

title: diabetic peach crumb bake
directions: Arrange peach slices in bottom of 8-inch square baking dish coated with cooking spray.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Combine butter, mustard, onion, poppy seed and horseradish for spread.
Slice dinner rolls with electric knife.
Use spread on both inside sides.
Place a piece of ham on each side and a slice of cheese in the middle.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Thinly slice with electric knife.

title: cranberry pot roast
directions: Dredge meat in flour; brown in hot fat.
Season meat; cover with unsweetened cranberry sauce and 1 cup hot water.
Cover closely; cook slowly about 3 hours or until tender.
Add more water, if necessary.
Remove roast to platter.
Thicken liquid for gravy.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: hopping john
directions: Simmer peas, ham hock, onion, celery and bay leaf covered until peas are tender.
Cook rice.
Combine peas, rice, ham and liquid from peas.
Simmer.

title: shrimp or lobster salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, catsup, and worcestershire sauce well and add to other ingredients.

title: chunky apple bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except apples and mix well.
Grease 1 Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans.
Put in a layer of batter then a layer of apple chunks.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Repeat 2 times.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Cover and chill until served.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: Place half a Hershey milk chocolate bar on a graham cracker half.

title: taco salad dip
directions: In a deep dish pie or pizza pan, spread sour cream evenly on bottom.
Next, spread shredded lettuce and then the taco sauce. Next, spread black olives, mushrooms and tomato, in that order. Top dish with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with taco chips. Great for football games and parties.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes in boiling water.
Drain well. Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs, cheese, pepper and onion. Pour into a 2-quart baking dish, greased.
Sprinkle with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until it bubbles and browns.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple yellow cake
directions: Bake yellow cake as usual.
Cool.
Blend milk, pudding and cream cheese with mixer.
Put this on cake.
Next, put pineapple on (well drained).
Top with Cool Whip, coconut and chopped walnuts.

title: blue ribbon chicken
directions: To form a pocket, cut each breast half horizontally, almost, but not, all the way through.
Cut each ham and cheese slice lengthwise in half.
Place a slice of each in each pocket. Combine bread crumbs and paprika.
Brush chicken with melted butter, then coat with crumbs.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Shape into loaf and cook in a loaf pan for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions together; drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving some of the crumbs and cheese. Pour into a casserole dish and sprinkle cheese and crumbs on top. Brown in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Add sugar to eggs, add margarine and vinegar and mix well. Fold in pecans, raisins and coconut, one at a time.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until brown and thick.

title: pie crusts
directions: Have pie pans sitting close by along with paper towels.
Work Crisco with a table knife and add ice water.
Work with hands and lots of extra flour on hands.
Work dough until all pie crust is off bowl.
Roll out dough to fit pie pans.
Use lots of flour on board and hands.
Stack with paper towel in between.
Put in plastic bags and freeze until needed.
Makes 10 pie crusts. Always have pie crusts in freezer and you will always be making lots of pies!

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Cream sugar and shortening, add egg and milk to shortening.
Add dry ingredients, when well mixed add boiling water and vanilla.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool and fill with frosting.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour; measure and sift again with baking powder and cocoa.
Sift 3 times; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Add flour mixture along with milk; add vanilla and beat well.
Bake 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan. Boil together the sugar, water, shortening, salt, raisins and spices for 5 minutes.
Cool completely. Add flour and baking soda (will be stiff).
Pour into tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean. Cool completely before turning out cake.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cool chicken.
Pull chicken from bones into bite size pieces. Mix soups and Veg-All together with chicken.
Cook bottom crust until it begins to brown (directions on box).
Fill with mixture. Place the other crust on top and fold down on sides.
Poke holes in top.
Cook, uncovered, until top crust turns brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: caramels
directions: Bring sugar, 1 cup cream and corn syrup to a boil, stirring constantly. Add the rest of the cream. Boil until 240° to 250°. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla. Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool. Cut and roll in wax paper.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add egg, flour, salt, baking powder and spices; mix.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mix. Chill in refrigerator.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: cracker pudding
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 15 minutes.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Melt margarine.
Add remaining ingredients, except for chicken.
Coat wings with this sauce.
Bake chicken on foil lined cookie sheets for 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.
Serve with Blue cheese dressing.

title: slaw
directions: Mash tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate. Will keep almost indefinitely.
Excellent on hot dogs or hamburgers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook, drain and cool chicken breasts. Mix all ingredients together. Either butter or spray casserole dish with Pam spray. Put ingredients in pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until it becomes thick.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile in saucepan, combine onions and ground beef.
Heat, stirring constantly, until onions are tender and meat browned. Remove from heat; blend in flour, pepper and salt.
Add catsup, Worcestershire sauce, mushrooms and buttermilk; mix well.
Stir noodles into beef mixture.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with onion rings, if desired.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Combine all ingredients together and use as desired with hot water, approximately 1/2 cup to each 1 cup of water.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning with mixer. Put in cake pan.
Then add a layer of salsa, layer of lettuce, tomato and then cheese.
Chill.
Serve with nacho cheese chips.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix and pour in a casserole dish sprayed with Pam the chicken, soups and vegetables.
Mix flour, milk and butter and spoon over pie.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: seafood dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except olives.
Garnish with olives.
Serve with crackers, chips, or raw vegetables.

title: pork chops creole
directions: Cut pork chops into 1-inch pieces; brown in a large skillet with 1 tablespoon oil.
Remove from pan.
In same skillet, saute onion, pepper and celery until they change color.
Add pork, spices and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for approximately 1 hour. Serve on a bed of rice.
Serves approximately 6 people.

title: mexican corn
directions: Heat oil in medium saucepan; saute peppers and onions over medium heat 5 minutes.
Add corn, tomatoes, pepper and salt.
Heat through.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: artichoke and pasta salad with tomato sauce
directions: Cook pasta until al dente and drain.
Transfer to a serving bowl and toss with 1/4 cup olive oil.
Drain marinade from the artichokes into a 10-inch skillet.
Set the artichokes aside.
Add the garlic and onions to the liquid and simmer until the onions become translucent.
Add the tomatoes, bay leaf, herbs and salt. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Uncover and cook another 10 minutes. Cut the artichokes in half and add to the tomato sauce.
Heat for a few minutes.
Remove the bay leaf and stir in the parsley.
Cool to room temperature and pour over the pasta.
Toss until well blended. Pass the Parmesan cheese separately.
Serves 6.

title: cobbler crumb mixture
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Add oil or applesauce and egg or egg whites.
Blend with a fork.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Put 3/4 of the mixture on a greased cookie sheet.
Put pie filling on mixture and spread the remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: saturday night supper
directions: Brown ground meat with chili powder.
Drain grease.
Add Spanish rice and beans.
Transfer to a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and top with cheese.
Heat in oven until cheese melts, then serve with chips.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all but chili sauce and jelly.
Gently form into 1-inch balls.
Brown in oven on cookie sheet at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Heat chili sauce and jelly in skillet, stirring constantly until jelly melts.
Add meatballs and stir until coated.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Serve hot in chafing dish.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: wine poached chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken and mushrooms in a large skillet; sprinkle with salt, tarragon, pepper and parsley.
Pour wine over chicken. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve with sauce left from skillet.
Makes 4 servings.

title: gay darlings moravin cookies(adapted to virginia by settlers from bohemia)
directions: Measure flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and baking soda into sifter.
Sift 3 times into medium bowl.
Cut in butter or oleo until mixture is like coarse cornmeal.
Add molasses and vinegar; stir until blended.
Cover and chill until firm.
Roll out and use favorite cookie cutters.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in oven at 350°. If in a hurry, roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake.

title: roxie's homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Combine hamburger and all other ingredients in a large pot.
Add water to desired consistency. Let simmer 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti noodles that have been boiled, drained and rinsed in cold water.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: grandma's favorite
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in a little milk at a time until the dough is soft and sticky.
Put the dough on a lightly floured surface; knead lightly.
Roll out and cut.
Place biscuits on a lightly greased pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: onion shrimp dip
directions: Mix Lipton onion soup mix and sour cream.
Chill for 1 hour, then add shrimp and horseradish.
Serve with all or any kind of fresh veggies.

title: corn bread
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, mixing well. Pour into well-greased 9-inch iron skillet.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute onion in small amount of cooking oil.
Add undrained corn, drained beans, tomato soup, rice, water, olives, chili powder, salt, oregano and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 30 minutes. Sprinkle crushed taco chips over the top.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: joyce's easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix together 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water.

title: quick and easy brunswick stew
directions: Mix and heat slowly.

title: fresh vegetable salad jellied
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in hot water.
Add cold water and vinegar.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Combine vegetables and fold into gelatin mixture.
Pour into molds or serving pan.
Chill until firm.
Serve on crisp lettuce.
Yield:
6 servings. Carbohydrate 2 g, protein 0 g, fat 0 g, calories 8. One serving = free food exchange.

title: remarkable fudge
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with foil. Extend foil over edges. Butter foil; set aside. Butter sides of a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
In it combine sugar, milk and margarine.

Cook and stir over medium-high heat to boiling. Clip candy thermometer to side of pan. Cook and stir over medium heat to 236°, soft ball stage (about 12 minutes). Remove saucepan from heat; remove thermometer. Add chocolate pieces, Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla. Stir until chocolate melts.
Spread into pan.
Score into squares while warm.
When firm, cut into squares.
Store in the refrigerator. Makes about 3 1/2 pounds (96 servings).

title: syrup bread
directions: Cream butter and syrup.
Add eggs and blend well.
Combine sifted flour and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, 10x sugar, Cool Whip and peanut butter.
Add the milk slowly with hand mixer.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Put mixture in pie crust; decorate with chocolate chips. Place pie in freezer for at least 24 hours.

title: potato and garlic soup with rosemary butter
directions: Bring chicken stock, diced potatoes and garlic cloves to boil in heavy large saucepan.
Reduce heat to medium and cook until potatoes and garlic are tender, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes.
Puree mixture in batches in blender or processor. Return to saucepan.
Stir in milk.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
(Can be made 1 day ahead to this point.
Cover and refrigerate.)
Mix butter and rosemary in small bowl.
Bring soup to simmer.
Ladle and top each with a small spoonful of rosemary butter.

title: artichoke delight
directions: Tear leaves away from hearts.
Mix leaves, mayonnaise and cheese together.
Place in greased casserole dish and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add milk and flour alternately. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easter cake
directions: Add salt to egg whites.
Beat until foamy.
Add cream of tartar, beat until stiff.
Then add sugar, a little at a time. Add flour and beat until smooth.
Pour in ungreased cake pan.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice and soy sauce.
Chill 2 hours or longer. Add green onion, celery, chestnuts, bean sprouts, salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and sprinkle with almonds and noodles.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hot chicken rice salad(casserole - one dish meal)
directions: Mix mayonnaise with soup, add remaining ingredients.
Put in buttered 8 x 13-inch pan.
Add topping and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chewies
directions: Melt margarine, stir in sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, then sifted flour and nuts.
This all stirred with a spoon.

title: senate restaurant bean soup
directions: Put peas or beans in large bowl.
Cover with 4 to 5 inches of water.
Soak overnight.
Drain the beans; run them under hot water until slightly whitened.
Put in large soup pot; cover with 3 quarts cold water.
Brown onions and garlic in a little butter. Add to beans.
Tie parsley, thyme, bay leaves, carrots and lemon in cheesecloth.
Add to beans.
Add ham hock.
Cook slowly for 3 hours.
Remove flavorings in cheesecloth and discard.
Remove ham hock and let cool.
Remove 2 cups beans with a little liquid. Puree and return with 2 cups water.
Cut ham into small pieces and return to soup.
Season with pepper and salt.
Reheat carefully. Serve with cornbread.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms, remove and chop stems.
Reserve mushroom caps.
Place chopped stems, green onions and butter in 1-quart microwave safe casserole.
Cook, uncovered, 3 to 4 minutes on High. Stir halfway through.
Mix in bread crumbs and parsley flakes. Stuff each mushroom cap and arrange in circle on paper towel-lined paper plate.
Cover with wax paper and microwave 1 to 2 minutes on High.

title: veal piccata
directions: Lightly coat veal with mixture of salt and flour.
In heavy skillet, melt butter and brown veal quickly.
Add wine, lemon juice and capers.
Cook a few minutes to reduce sauce slightly. Use lemon slices and parsley as a garnish.

title: curried chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and cheese.
Spoon into buttered 3-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs, then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until cheese melts, and sauce is bubbly.

title: chocolate delights
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, whisk together sugar, walnuts, cocoa powder and salt.
Add the egg whites and vanilla; stir until combined well.
Form rounded tablespoons of the mixture into balls.
Put balls on baking sheets lined with parchment paper (brown paper bag).
With the bottom of a glass, press them gently into disks.
Bake cookies in the oven for 15 to 17 minutes (tops will appear dry and lighter in color).

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in blender at high speed.
Add poppy seed with blender on high speed.
Add oil slowly.

title: pork chops with thyme sauce
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon margarine; saute onion until tender. Remove; keep warm.
Combine garlic powder, flour, sage and thyme. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add the remaining margarine; brown chops.
Remove to platter.
Pour off excess fat.
Add broth; bring to boil.
Place chops in pan, cover and reduce heat.
Baste with pan juice during cooking.
Cook for 25 to 30 minutes until tender. Remove to serving platter.

title: janie's cheese and bacon cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients in order given.
Serve on crackers.
Keeps for days.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, beaten egg, dates and sprinkle baking soda over dates.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Let cool and add flour, baking powder, pinch of salt and nuts.
Bake up to 1 hour at 350° in medium greased and floured tubular pan.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil broccoli; drain and put in bottom of casserole.
Put chicken on top of broccoli and cover with mixture of soup, mayonnaise, and lemon juice. Put cheese on top.
Sprinkle dressing on top of cheese.
Bake in 350° for 35 minutes.

title: galician broth(serves 6)
directions: Divide the chicken into pieces at joints; cut beef, ham and salt pork into small pieces.
To the water, add meats, beans, onion, garlic and tomatoes; cook to a broth.
Season and add potatoes, turnips and cabbage.
When these vegetables are done and before serving, add about a tablespoon olive oil and a teaspoon vinegar or sour orange juice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream and soup.
Melt margarine and add cracker crumbs.
Put chicken mixture into ovenproof dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs, margarine and poppy seed mixture.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: heavenly jam
directions: Boil together
first
ingredients
about 20 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in jello until dissolved.
Pour into jars. Either freeze or seal.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and 1 cup of noodles.
Pour into 2-quart flat casserole. Sprinkle with noodles and toasted almonds. Salt.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: corn-stuffed onions(6 servings)
directions: Hollow out onions.
Chop centers to make 1 cup; fill onions with corn.
Place in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook, covered, in microwave on "Cook" for 16 minutes, turning dish once.
In a 4-cup glass measuring bowl, combine butter and chopped onions. Cook, uncovered, in microwave on Cook for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in soup and any remaining corn and cheese.
Cook at "Cook" for 1 minute, stirring once.
Spoon sauce over onions; cook, uncovered, at Cook for 6 minutes.
Total cooking time:
26 minutes.

title: old fashioned corn cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and fry in greased skillet.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes, mash, beat in cream cheese, sour cream, salt & pepper.
When light and fluffy put into a greased 9 X 13 baking dish.
Cover with foil and refrigerate up to 1 week.
Bake before serving.
Dot with butter, sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spiced cucumbers
directions: Cut cucumbers lengthwise and de-seed; cut into slices.
Place all ingredients in plastic container with sealable lid.
Place in refrigerator, turning over and over for 2 days.

title: pork stir-fry
directions: In a medium bowl, combine sherry, cornstarch and spices.
Add pork and toss until
meat is evenly coated.
Heat oil over medium-high heat in skillet.
Add pork mixture and cook, stirring frequently, about 5 minutes.
Add pepper, mushrooms and onion. Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Serve over hot spinach linguine.

title: swedish sugar cookies
directions: Cream granulated sugar, powdered sugar, oleo and oil together. Add egg and vanilla.
Mix in another bowl plain flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill until cool.
Roll in marble size balls and roll in bowl of granulated sugar.
Place on foil covered cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes or until outer edges begin to lightly brown.

title: quick crisp
directions: Dump pie filling into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread cake mix on top.
Evenly place cut butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn souffle
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour.
Add milk. Cook until thick. Beat egg yolks.
Add corn.
Combine sauce, corn mixture, cheese and salt.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold in.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: raisin applesauce cake(diabetic)
directions: Cook raisins in water on high until all water is gone.
Do not scorch.
In large mixing bowl mix applesauce, eggs, oil and sweetener.
Mix well.
Sift flour, soda and cinnamon together. Add raisins.
Then add vanilla and flour, cinnamon and soda mixture.
Blend together.
Add fruit and nuts.
Stir well with spoon.
Pour into a well-greased and floured Bundt pan or tube. Cook at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Test with toothpick for doneness.
It will be moist.

title: out of the blue great dinner
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni as directed on box.
Put shrimp in bowl after washing thoroughly.
Add 2 tablespoons Worcestershire.
Mix through shrimp.
In large skillet, add olive oil.
Add shrimp; cook on medium heat until shrimp turns red.
Serve over rice. Serves 4.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Drain yams.
Reserve 1/2 cup sugar.
Slice yams in half.
Mix cornstarch with yam-syrup and lemon juice.
Place half of yam slices on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Top with half the raisins and apples.
Sprinkle with pinch of salt, half the sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and dot half the butter.
Pour half the syrup.
Mix over layers.
Repeat layers.
Top with pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: gourmet spinach
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package.
Drain well. Place in greased 11 x 7-inch glass pan.
Top with mushrooms and 4 strips bacon.
Cook 20 minutes at 325°.
Cover with sour cream and Cheddar.
Cook 10 minutes more.

title: hawaiian fried rice
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms in bacon drippings. Add cooked rice and beaten egg. Mix thoroughly. Add soy sauce and black pepper. Cook just until egg is set. Serve immediately.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Pour over corn, candy and peanuts.
Mix well. Press firmly into angel food cake pan.
Cool several hours. Slice.

title: crisp oven fried chicken
directions: Combine crackers, cheese, parsley, salt, oregano, basil, celery, and onion salt, paprika, pepper, and bay leaf in bowl. Dip chicken pieces in evaporated milk and then coat with crumb mixture.
Place chicken in shallow, ungreased roasting pan, skin side up.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Brush with oil; continue baking 30 more minutes or until golden brown and tender. Yields 8 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage in pan and drain.
Melt oleo in long pyrex dish. Break up bread and stir in margarine to coat.
Place sausage over bread crumbs.
Beat eggs and mustard.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour milk and eggs over other ingredients.
Top with grated cheese. Can be placed in refrigerator overnight.
I find it is better. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 min.

title: corn sausa
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Great with big corn chips.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, cornstarch and salt together.
Add milk. Cook until thick.
Beat eggs.
Add some of the hot mixture to the eggs, then add to the rest of the hot mixture and cook for 2 minutes.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Put in baked pie shell.
Use the 3 egg whites for meringue.

title: easy cobbler
directions: In 1-quart shallow casserole, combine fruit, plain sugar, 1 tablespoon baking mix and cinnamon.
In medium bowl, mix remaining 2/3 cup baking mix with brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is size of small peas.
Stir in milk until moistened.
Drop by spoonfuls onto fruit mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted into crust comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, 1/2 stick margarine, onion, mushroom soup, sour cream and salt and pepper to taste.
Put in baking dish.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and cook in water; drain and mash.
Mix next 4 ingredients into squash.
Prepare stuffing mix according to directions on box, except use 1 stick butter instead of 1/2 stick. Mix stuffing into squash mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: apple coffee cake(kosher)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix pie filling and cinnamon; reserve.
Beat flour, sugar, milk, softened margarine, baking powder, salt and eggs in large bowl on low speed, about 30 seconds.
Beat at medium speed (2 minutes).
Pour 1/2 of batter (about 2 cups) into pan.
Spoon 1/2 of pie filling (about 1 cup) over batter in pan.
Repeat with remaining batter and pie mixture.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over top of pie filling mixture; drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake until wooden toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, about 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: zucchini apricot jam
directions: Put zucchini and sugar into pot and bring to a boil for 6 minutes. Add pineapple and boil 6 minutes. Remove from heat and add apricot jello. Stir well and pour into 1/2 pint jars and seal. Boil in hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake; cookies will be soft.
They puff during baking, then flatten upon cooling.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: montana goulash
directions: Brown hamburger with onion (chopped) and mushrooms. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Add corn; simmer while cooking macaroni. Add macaroni and stir all together.

Bake in a 300° oven for 30 minutes or so. Add tomato juice, if more moisture is needed. Top with grated cheeses and continue cooking until cheeses are melted and bubbly. Serve with French or garlic bread.

title: creamed tacos
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cream and chips, together and place in crock-pot and cook on low for at least 2 hours.
This may be cooked all day if desired.
Add cream 15 minutes before serving and serve over tortilla chips.

title: rolls
directions: Mix sugar, salt and melted shortening in mixing bowl.
Add boiling water and stir, then add cold water.
Cool to lukewarm. Add egg which has been beaten.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Add dissolved yeast and mix.
Add flour in 1/2 cup portions.
When dough follows spoon, enough flour has been added. Put in greased mixing bowl and let rise until double in bulk. Knead for 8 to 10 minutes.
Shape in desired shape.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: 10 minute orange fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatins in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add orange juice concentrate; stir until dissolved.
Stir in pineapple.
Chill until partially congealed.
Fold in bananas and whipped cream. Chill until firm.
Yields 12 servings.

title: wild rice-chicken supreme
directions: Cook, debone and cube chicken.
Cook rice as directed on package and set aside.
Saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add cream and chicken broth.
Cook until thickened.
Mix sauce with chicken, pimientos, parsley and almonds.
Add to cooked rice.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes in a 2-quart casserole.
May be frozen before cooking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers.
Remove seeds.
Mix beef with rice, onion, salt, pepper and garlic.
Fill peppers with meat mixture. Arrange tightly in 3-quart casserole so one pepper is in center of dish.
Mix together soup and water.
Pour over and around peppers.
Insert temperature probe so tip is in middle of center pepper. Cover tightly with plastic wrap, arranging loosely around probe to vent.
Attach cable end in receptacle.
Cook on High for 28 to 32 minutes, turning every 7 minutes or or 175° with probe.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Cheese may be placed over peppers while standing.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for 2 hours and serve. Serves approximately 10.

title: harvest beets
directions: Cover 1 package of small dried lima beans with water.
Soak overnight; pour off water.
Cover again with fresh water; simmer until barely tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour off water.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate.
Cream butter until soft and gradually stir in sugar until dissolved.
Stir in eggs. Sift flour with pinch of salt and put into mixture.
Stir in nuts, chocolate and vanilla.
Pour mixture into 8-inch square pan.
Bake in oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pork cutlets with apple-cranberry sauce
directions: Using meat mallet or rolling pin, pound pork slices to 1/8-inch thickness between 2 sheets of plastic wrap.
In shallow dish, combine flour, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper. Dip cutlets into flour mixture to coat on both sides, shaking off excess and setting aside any remaining flour mixture.

title: lisa's trash
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter and morsels together.
Melt over medium heat.
In a large bowl, mix peanuts and cereal; pour chocolate sauce over dry mixture and mix well.
Put powdered sugar in white trash bag.
Put mixture in the bag and shake well.
Pour back into large bowl.

title: garden potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes; boil in jackets until tender.
Cool and peel. Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Add celery, green onion and parsley.

title: chicken bake
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Top with Rice Krispies and bake additional 10 minutes. Serves 6.

title: fresh vegetable appetizer
directions: Spread rolls on large cookie sheet, pressing together at seams to cover entire bottom of sheet.
Bake by instructions until brown. Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dry dressing. Mix together and spread on cool bread.
Mix vegetables and sprinkle over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares.

title: corn bread pie
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and salt; drain.
Mix water, tomato soup and black pepper with beef.
Simmer in skillet for 15 minutes.
Pour in large casserole dish.
In separate bowl, mix corn meal, sugar, flour, egg, bacon grease and milk.
Mix; pour over top of other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lye soap
directions: Make soap on first quarter of the moon.
Put 3 gallons of fat in an old black wash pot.
Add 1 can Red Devil lye.
Bring to a boil.
Boil unti lye eats the meat up.
Pour 1 gallon water in the pot.
Bring to a boil and boil until water boils away.
Dip out and pour into pan.
Let cool.
Cut out blocks of soap.

title: wassail
directions: Combine sugar and water; bring to a boil.
Add cloves, cinnamon and ginger.
Cover and let stand in a warm place 1 hour; strain.
Add orange juice, lemon juice and cider.
Bring to a boil and serve at once.
Serves 100.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Boil together sugar, oil, vinegar, water, salt and pepper and cool. Mix peas, corn, pimentos, green pepper, celery and green onions. Pour the boiled mixture over the vegetables. Mix and refrigerate.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt in a bowl.
Mix together the margarine and eggs; beat well.
Add egg mixture to sugar mixture along with milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake for 15 to 20 minutes more or until done.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all together. It is better if refrigerated for awhile.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup; cook until it threads.
Before done, beat egg whites.
Have ready to pour in hot ingredients. Beat until gloss is gone.
Put in vanilla and pecans and mix with spoon.
Spoon out on wax paper.
Remember to use a glass bowl to beat.
Keep hot ingredients stirred.

title: italian zucchini crescent pizza
directions: Cook and stir zucchini and onion in butter for 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in parsley flakes, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano.
Combine eggs and cheese; stir into zucchini mix.
Spray 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish with Pam or no grease at all; cover bottom with rolls.
Spread mustard over roll crust.
Pour zucchini mix over this.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until center is set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: homemade pastry and chicken the easy way
directions: Boil chicken until done (season as desired).
Let cool. Separate chicken form the bone and skin.
Put chicken back into water.
Roll biscuits out like pastry, keeping covered with flour. Roll each biscuit separately.
Roll out until it is about 6-inches in diameter, flipping it over and covering with flour each time.
Cut into slices about 1-inch wide.

title: marinara sauce (tomato)
directions: Brown garlic cloves lightly in olive oil.
Use 2-quart saucepan.
Set aside until slightly cool.
Add the two cans of crushed tomatoes, salt and oregano.
Allow to simmer slowly, about 1 hour.
Serve on any recipe requiring Marinara sauce.

title: syble's chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil hen or chicken in seasoned water until tender; cool. Remove from bones and cut into bite sized pieces.
Return to broth.

title: never-fail meringue
directions: Blend cornstarch and cold water in saucepan.
Add boiling water and cook, stirring, until clear and thickened.
Let stand until completely cold.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Turn mixer to low speed and add salt and vanilla.
Gradually beat in cold cornstarch mixture.
Beat well.
Spread on pie.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken noodle dumplings
directions: Place whole chicken in a deep, heavy pot; cover with water and boil until almost done.
Add bouillon cubes and chicken broth; cover and let stand 30 minutes.

title: 24 hour cole slaw
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, salt, mustard and celery seed in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add oil.
Mix. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over shredded cabbage and onion. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Keeps in refrigerator for 7 to 10 days.

title: virginia pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and add alternately with milk.
Beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Pour into Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: homemade beef salami
directions: First Day:
Mix in a large bowl; cover and refrigerate.

title: banana cream pie(from eagle products)
directions: Dissolve cornstarch and salt in water.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Cool slightly.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Prepare the orange Jell-O using 1 cup of hot water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Repeat for the cherry and lime Jell-Os.
Pour into separate ice trays; chill until firm.

title: turkey quesadilla
directions: Mix together meat, cheese, onion and pepper.
Spread mixture over 1 tortilla and top with another.
Cook on medium heat in a skillet with a small amount of butter or oil.
Turn once to brown both sides lightly.
Slice into 4 wedges each.
Top with salsa and sour cream.

title: lime-pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water. Dissolve cream cheese in 3/4 cup hot water and mix with Jell-O. Add pineapple and nuts. Stir together and chill until firm. Use a 9 x 13 dish or a smaller size for a thicker salad.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; add Ranch dressing.
Let chill for 20 minutes.
Roll into finely chopped nuts and parsley flakes, shaping into ball.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: combination casserole
directions: Saute beef, bell pepper and onion until beef is cooked.
Drain fat and set aside.
Cook noodles until just tender.
Drain and set aside.
Add all remaining ingredients except cheese to the beef. Mix well, then add noodles.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into a large baking dish and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover, sprinkle with cheese and return to oven for 10 more minutes.

title: sharon's spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Stir in Ragu sauce.
Layer meat sauce with cheeses.
Pour mushroom soup over casserole and top with layer of cheese and olives.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Combine beaten eggs, corn syrup, vanilla, sugar and melted butter.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in 1/2 of the pecans.
Pour the mixture into the unbaked pie shell.
Put the remaining pecans on top of pie.
Bake in oven at 350° from 45 to 60 minutes.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into small wedges.
Cook in salted water until tender.
Drain well.
In a casserole dish, put in alternate layers of cabbage, soup, milk and cheese.
Top with bread crumbs.
Dot generously with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until bubbly and browned.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: poached fish dinner with mustard-dill sauce
directions: Steam potatoes and carrots for 15 minutes.
Add zucchini and steam for additional 10 minutes or until desired texture is reached.
Bring poaching ingredients (water, lemon juice, lemon peel, onion, parsley and bay leaf) to a boil in a broad, shallow pan or skillet.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes to extract flavor from seasoning.
Add fish; simmer, partially covered, 10 minutes, or until fish flakes with a fork.

title: angel food trifle
directions: Mix together Ricotta cheese and yogurt in blender or food processor until smooth. Arrange half of cake cubes in bottom of a medium size glass bowl. Top with 1 cup of the berries. Top with 1 1/2 cups of cheese-yogurt mixture. Decorate with the remaining 1/4 cup berries. Top each serving with 1 tablespoon Cool Whip.

title: corn casserole
directions: Place corn in large bowl.
Add butter, eggs, corn meal, salt, sour cream and cheese.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water.
Brown meat and onion together in skillet and drain very well.
Add the tomatoes, soup and sugar and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes (until well heated).
Add the spaghetti.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan and top with 4 strips of lean bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and water exactly 1 minute.
Pour over peanut butter and vanilla in a bowl.
Beat with mixer for 2 minutes on slow.
Pour into greased pan.

title: chicken-dressing casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Place in bottom of 9 x 12-inch dish. Mix soups and milk together.
Pour over chicken.
Mix chicken broth and oleo together; add stuffing mix (this will be thin when first mixed).
Spoon on top of chicken and soup mixture.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° or until brown.
You may add sage to dressing, if desired.

title: appalachian red grape spread
directions: Peel skins off grapes and set aside.
Simmer peeled grapes in a saucepan until tender.
Remove from heat and remove seeds with a drainer spoon.
Add skins, vinegar and sugar; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add cinnamon and cloves and boil for 10 minutes.
Pour into sterilized canning jars and seal tightly.
Store in cellar or a cool, dry place.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Line top and sides with waxed paper.
Grease waxed paper.
Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in pumpkin, then stir in dry ingredients.
Spread evenly into pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes.
Invert onto towel dusted with powdered sugar.
Peel off waxed paper.
Roll up cake and towel together from short side. Place open side down on wire rack.
Cool completely.
Unroll cake. Spread with filling of your choice and reroll until ready to serve.

title: italian stir-fry chicken
directions: Put 1/2 cup to 3/4 cup of Parmesan dressing into electric frypan.
Add chicken and stir-fry 5 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Add more dressing and stir-fry frozen vegetables 5 minutes.
Put chicken back in and cook until vegetables are done.
Serve over cooked spaghetti noodles.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: apple marmalade
directions: Quarter unpeeled orange; remove seeds and thinly slice.
In an 8 to 10-quart kettle or Dutch oven, combine the first 3 ingredients and 2 cups water.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer until apples are tender.
Add sugar.
Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir until thickened and clear.
Remove from heat.
Skim off foam.
Pour at once into hot, sterilized jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust lids. Process in boiling water bath (half pints) for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 half pints.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients just until sugar melts and put aside to cool.
Then mix pudding and milk and add sour cream.
Fold in 3/4 of the carton of Cool Whip.
Layer a dish with vanilla wafers, pudding mix and strawberries.
Continue layering until top of dish and then ice with remaining Cool Whip.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven.
Mix cake as directed on package.
Fill paper cups in muffin tins 2/3 full.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop teaspoons of cream cheese mixture onto center of each cupcake.
Bake as directed on cake mix package.

title: cottage cheese fruit salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese.
Mix well.
Add drained fruit and blend.
Blend Cool Whip into mixture.
Keep refrigerated.

title: take along breakfast cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt. Mix well and set aside. Cream butter and sugar. beat in egg and vanilla. Add flour mixture, mixing well. Stir in oats, cheese, wheat germ and bacon. Drop by rounded tbsp. onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 16 minutes. Cool one minute on cookie sheet.

title: olive balls
directions: Heat oven to 400°.

title: haystacks(cookies)
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels on low heat, then add peanuts and chow mein noodles.
Drop onto wax paper by spoonfuls.
Let cool.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine peas, eggs, green pepper, onion and cheese in a serving dish. Fold in mayonnaise. Season with white pepper; top with bacon. Chill several hours before serving.

title: hummus
directions: Spread bread with a little olive oil and bake for 10 minutes. Mash the chickpeas into a thick paste in food processor or blender or with a fork.
Add all the remaining ingredients.
Chill and season to taste.
Dip pita bread into the hummus or use it as a dip with cut vegetables.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: In large saucepan, brown meat; drain.
Remove half of meat; set aside.
Stir tomato sauce, paste, water and brown sugar into meat.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, combine remaining meat, Ricotta, 2 cups Mozzarella, egg and parsley.

title: chocolate peanut-butter cup cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium size bowl combine flour, cocoa powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter, peanut butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar and vanilla about 3 minutes until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat until thoroughly blended after each addition.
Reduce speed to low; gradually beat in flour mixture until smooth.
Stir in peanut butter cup pieces into dough along with chocolate chips.
Drop dough, 3 tablespoons per cookie, onto ungreased cookie sheet, spacing about 1 inch apart.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes until dry and slightly firm to touch.

title: tuna salad
directions: Drain cans of tuna.
Put into large bowl.
Boil noodles and drain.
Combine all ingredients together.
Stir.
Serve warm or cool.

title: riskrem
directions: Boil together the first 3 ingredients on medium heat or low heat. Stir frequently until rice is tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Remove from heat and cool. Stir off and on so no crust forms. Whip the whipping cream. Add sugar to taste and vanilla.
Fold whipping cream into rice. Serve with berry syrup.

title: sausage appetizers
directions: Mix together in crock-pot.
Cook on high for one hour.
Leave on low until ready to serve.

title: mexican meat loaves
directions: Empty seasoned coating mix into shaker bag.
Combine ground beef, corn, onion, chili powder and egg.
Form into 8 small loaves.
Carefully shake each loaf in shaker bag until evenly coated.
Place in ungreased shallow baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and top each loaf with 1 teaspoon ketchup.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: quick chocolate turtles
directions: Melt the almond bark following directions.
Take 2 pecan halves and press one on the side of cut caramel square.
Dip into chocolate.
Use slotted spoon to allow excess to drain off.
Place on wax paper.
Cool 30 minutes.

title: homemade cracker jacks
directions: Set popcorn aside in a large shallow pan. Boil together butter, sugar and vinegar for 5 minutes; remove from heat and add syrup, soda, vanilla and peanuts. Pour over popcorn and stir until well coated. Bake 1 hour at 275° to 300°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: sugar bacon
directions: Beat mustard, Worcestershire, sugar and egg yolks together. Dip bacon in mixture and roll in crumbs.
Place bacon in a broiler pan.
Bake in a preheated 250° oven for 20 minutes or until brown and crispy.
Yields 20 slices.

title: mock lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Brown beef in 1 tablespoon butter in medium skillet; stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat and set aside.

title: hot tuna sandwiches
directions: Combine tuna, pepper, celery and onion.
Moisten with mayonnaise.
Spread on muffin halves.
Place under preheated broiler 2 to 3 minutes.
Top with cheese; broil 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: asparagus delight
directions: Grease oblong casserole with oleo.
Drain asparagus and put in bottom of casserole.
Drain peas, slice water chestnuts and sprinkle over asparagus.
Heat
soup and pour over asparagus. Sprinkle cheese over
soup.
Melt
butter over low heat. Trim bread and cut into small finger size strips.
Soak strips in butter and lay strips
over
cheese.
Bake
in 350° oven 25 minutes or until bread
is
golden
brown.
May be made ahead, refrigerated and then baked.

title: pat's four layer dessert
directions: Combine flour, nuts, margarine and sugar.
Spread into a 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool.
For second layer, combine softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
For third layer, combine the pudding mix and milk; beat until thickened.
Pour over the second layer. Spread Cool Whip on top; sprinkle with nuts if desired.
Chill.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saute sausage and onions.
Drain. Combine other ingredients except biscuits.
Place in an 11 x 7-inch oblong baking dish.
May refrigerate overnight. Divide biscuits in halves or fourths and place on top. Bake at 350° until biscuits are brown. Serves 6 to 8.

title: elephant stew
directions: Remove sausage from casings.
In large, covered casserole dish, cook sausage, onion and garlic on High 2 1/2 to 4 minutes (depending on microwave) until no longer pink.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Drain drippings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze spinach until dry.
Cut up.
Stir together spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and onions; blend well.
Cover and refrigerate two hours.
Stir before serving.
NOTE:
Can be put inside a hollowed out center of pumpernickel bread.
Cut the inside part that was cut out, into cubes and use with dip.

title: chicken-biscuit bake
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Cool and cut into small pieces. Reserve liquid.
Peel and dice potatoes and carrots; boil approximately 10 minutes or just until tender.
Drain water. Drain liquid from can of peas and mix peas together with chicken, potatoes, carrots and soup mixed with reserved liquid from chicken.
Put in a large baking dish and top with refrigerated biscuits (or your favorite biscuits).
Bake at 400° until biscuits are golden brown.
Serve hot from the oven.

title: mushroom business
directions: Note:
Adjust mushrooms and bread to taste and to size of dish.

title: very blueberry cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight container.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup.
Mix with boiling water.
Adjust amount, depending on size of cup/mug.
This makes a nice gift.
Just put the mix in a decorative jar.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs; gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy and light colored.
Add flour sifted with baking powder and salt.
Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Heat milk with butter almost to boiling and stir quickly into batter.
Beat slightly.
Pour at once into ungreased 9 or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until done.
Remove from oven and invert pan until cool, then remove cake.
Delicious unfrosted.

title: swiss steak the easy way
directions: Sprinkle steak with onion soup mix.
Place steak on heavy aluminum foil.
Bring foil over top of meat and fold to seal. Place foil-covered steak in an open pan.

title: nutmeg feather cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour and both sugars.
Beat until well mixed.
Add melted butter and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Pour in pie shell and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: egg in a hole
directions: Cut center out of slice of bread with a round cookie cutter or glass. Butter both sides of remaining bread, using about 1/2 tablespoon butter. Melt remaining tablespoon butter in a small skillet over medium heat. Brown one side of bread in skillet; turn bread over. Break egg into a small cup or saucer. Carefully slip it into the hole in the bread slice in the skillet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cook egg until white is set, then turn egg and bread over with spatula to brown other side.

title: butter bean zesty bake
directions: Brown onion and green pepper in butter. Add remaining ingredients except beans.
Heat.
Pour beans in a buttered 1-quart casserole.
Pour sauce over the beans.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Combine 8 oz. French Vanilla Cool Whip, 8 oz. cream cheese and 1/3 cup of sugar.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate overnight and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and add sugars (may use all brown sugar), oil and maple flavoring.
Mix well.
Add zucchini, baking powder, soda, salt, wheat germ and flour.
Mix well, then add nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: giant pot pie
directions: Cook vegetables until nearly tender.
Combine with meat.
Pour into big casserole dish.
Set aside.
Meanwhile, blend butter and flour with stock or milk and cook until it begins to thicken. Pour over vegetables and meat mixture.
Adjust pastry over casserole.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400° if using air bake sheet; for regular baking sheet, bake at 350°. Mix butter, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla thoroughly. Work in flour, salt and nuts until dough holds together. Shape into 3/4-inch balls. Place 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes but do not let brown. While warm, roll in confectioners sugar, then cool and roll in sugar once more. Makes 4 dozen. Can double recipe. Freezes well.

title: four layer cake
directions: 1st layer: Mix flour and margarine together in sheet pan. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced meatballs
directions: Combine in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Saute in 2 to 3 tablespoons butter until well browned. Drain well and set aside.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Saute hamburger and onions.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Make crust of Bisquick and cream.
Pat crust into 9-inch pie pan.
Pour hamburger mixture in pie crust. Combine eggs and cheese; spread over hamburger mixture.
Sprinkle paprika over all.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ja's favorite chicken bake
directions: Stew chicken until tender and remove bones.
Mix soups, Ro-Tel and cheese.
Simmer together until cheese is melted.
In baking dish, place 1/2 of deboned chicken.
Put a layer of Doritos over chicken, then pour 1/2 of sauce over Doritos.
Repeat layers. Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put half of the raw ground beef (ground chuck) into the bottom of a greased casserole and cover with half of the potatoes, sliced thick, half of the carrots, sliced and half of the onion, minced. Sprinkle with half of the salt and some pepper.
Repeat with other half of ingredients.
Mix soup and water and pour over top.
Bake at 350°
for 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are tender.

title: red velvet cake
directions: In small bowl mix cake flour, cocoa powder and baking soda.
In large bowl mix together with a beater the sugar, vanilla and butter; then add eggs, beating in one at a time.
Add food color and vinegar.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl well.
Then pour mixture out of small bowl into large bowl.
Finally add buttermilk and mix.
Pour batter into three 9-inch round pans.
Bake at 350°.

title: mama's pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and pineapple juice.
Let simmer for 10 minutes.
Add Jell-O.
Chill.
Beat chilled milk.
Add to Jell-O mixture.
Pour into 2 pie crusts made of vanilla wafers.
Makes 2 pies.

title: crab stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Drain crab meat on several layers of paper towels.
Thinly slice tops and bottoms from tomatoes.
With a small melon ball cutter, remove pulp and drain upside-down on paper towels.

title: tuscany chicken
directions: Pound chicken flat; dust with flour.
Dip in egg batter. Dredge in bread crumbs, Parmesan and herbs which you've mixed together.
Heat butter and olive oil in large skillet (1/2 at a time).
Saute chicken until brown.
Do this in 2 batches.
Serve over vermicelli and cheese.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, water Jell-O in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Let boil approximately 1 minute.
Cool.
Add strawberries. Pour into baked pie shell.
Add topping (Cool Whip preferred).
Let chill and serve.

title: diabetic ice cream
directions: Mix sweetener, flour and then eggs.
Add cool whip and flavoring.
Add 2% milk to above in freezer to fill up.
Proceed to freeze as regular ice cream.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix together.
Pour into a gallon freezer.
Add enough milk to bring mixture to full line.
Stir well.
Freeze.

title: henry bain sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve over cream cheese with crackers. Keep sauce in refrigerator and use as needed.
This is a very good appetizer.

title: broccoli-stuffed tomatoes *
directions: Season tomatoes with vegetable seasoning.
Place broccoli, onion, bread crumbs, parsley, basil and yogurt in bowl.
Mix lightly with fork.
Stuff tomato halves with broccoli mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Place in shallow ovenproof baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or microwave, covered, on High 2 minutes.

title: fish chowder
directions: Place bacon in heavy kettle and fry slowly until golden brown, eating some as you go.
Add the onion and cook until they are soft and light yellow in color.
Add potatoes and sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste, then add water to cover the potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are half finished, then add the fish on top of the potatoes and cook until fish is done and can be broken into flakes.
If there is skin on the fish, remove it before breaking up fish.
Add milk until it looks like creamed chowder and then add the corn.
Cook until heated but do not boil.

title: steak diane
directions: Place steaks between waxed paper and pound slightly with rolling pin or hands.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a pan.
Add green onions.
Saute for a few minutes.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, parsley and lemon juice.
Heat through.
Keep warm.
Melt and heat remaining butter in another skillet.
Add steaks to pan. Saute quickly, about 2 minutes per side.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spoon the butter-onion mixture over steaks in pan.
At this point, you may flame the steaks, if desired.
Heat cognac or brandy, pour over steaks in pan. Ignite.
Place hot steaks on serving dish.
Pour pan juices over.
Sprinkle with green onion and lemon peel.
Serve immediately.
Makes four servings.

title: irish soda bread
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Combine 1 egg and buttermilk; stir into flour mixture, just until moistened.
Fold in raisins.

title: mock duck in orange sauce
directions: Salt and pepper the chicken; place on a rack in a roasting pan.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes or until brown and tender.

title: beef brisket
directions: Sprinkle celery salt, garlic salt, lemon pepper, onion salt and liquid smoke over meat. Wrap in heavy foil and refrigerate overnight. Add salt and pepper and worcestershire sauce. Cook 5 hours at 300°. After 5 hours, add a small bottle of BBQ sauce. Cook, uncovered, for 1 hour. Set out 20 minutes before serving.

title: chili mostaccioli
directions: Combine meat, milk, crumbs, salt and pepper; shape into 5 oblong patties.
In a pan, brown patties in hot shortening. Remove.
Cook garlic and onion in skillet until tender, not brown. Blend in soup and water.
Return patties to skillet.
Bring mixture to boil; simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
Cook mostaccioli according to package directions; drain.
Place on large heated plater.
Arrange patties on noodles.
Pour sauce over meat. Sprinkle cheese atop.
Serves 5.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, oleo and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Blend and shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: tuna cabbage hong kong
directions: Drain vegetable
oil
into large skillet, very hot, add onion and saute a few minutes, toss in cabbage and saute about five minutes,
stirring
occasionally.
Stir in tuna, tomatoes and soy sauce.
Cover
and
continue
to
cook five minutes or longer. Serve immediately.
Makes two or three servings.

title: easy to do fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, mix sugar, milk and butter.
Bring to boil. Boil for 5 minutes; stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Beat marshmallow cream, peanut butter, chocolate chips and vanilla until smooth and creamy.
Pour into two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Makes 6 pounds fudge.

title: lasagna roll-ups(makes 10 to 12 roll-ups.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine egg, Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, 1 ounce only Mozzarella cheese, oregano and garlic powder.
Spread cheese mixture equally on lasagna noodle strips; roll up each strip.
Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Spread 1 cup sauce in bottom of baking dish.
Arrange lasagna rolls, seam side down, in sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over lasagna and top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Cover tightly; bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: garlic bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Take large piece of aluminum foil and place loaf of bread in middle.
Slice and drizzle garlic butter onto slices.
Wrap with foil and bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes or take slices of bread, drizzle butter on it and broil until golden brown.
Refrigerate leftover butter to use another time.

title: pea salad
directions: Layer each item on top of the other as they were listed. Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Combine tea, sugar, orange mix, lemonade mix and spices in a bowl, mixing well.
Store in airtight container.
Add 2 to 3 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water to serve.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: At end of cooking time, remove tomatoes from this solution and continue to cook liquid down to a slightly thick syrup.
Pack tomatoes into sterilized jars, cover with syrup and seal.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternating with flour.
Add flavoring.
Put in sour cream and soda.
Bake at 350°.

title: pecan nibbles
directions: Put pecans in 250° to 275° oven approximately 25 minutes. Melt bark in double boiler or microwave. Mix pecans and grahams in bowl.
Pour melted bark over them. Mix well, then pour on wax paper and spread. When cold, break apart.

title: chicken-n-rice soup
directions: Boil chicken in water until done, then remove.
Add potatoes, celery, onion, rice and bouillon cubes to chicken stock.
While the rice and vegetables are boiling, cut up the chicken and add. Simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In 2 to 4-quart saucepan, mix sugar and milk.
Cook on low heat until forms a ball stage.
Stir mixture while cooking.
To check for ball stage, drop drops from your spoon on a plate and let cool.
Use your fingertip to see if it will roll up to ball stage.
When ball stage, take off stove.
Add 3 to 4 big spoons of peanut butter.
It may take more to be thick.
Pour out on buttered surface.

title: dilly beans
directions: Snap off the ends of beans; leave them whole.
Cook beans; bring to a rolling boil.
Drain and cool.
Place beans, standing up, in pint jars.
Place flower of dill in the bottom of each jar. Place water, vinegar and salt in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over beans in jar.
Seal and store.

title: hard candy(rock)
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in a saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat until mixture reaches 300° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add flavoring and a few drops of food coloring.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Boil carrots and potatoes for 5 minutes.
Add soups, soy sauce, water, carrots and potatoes to browned meat and onions.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Add egg noodles to top of casserole and cook for 1 hour more.

title: hot dish
directions: Fry hamburger and onion.
First put in a layer of Tater Tots, then your hamburger, then a layer of beans, then a layer of soup and pour 1 can of milk over all.
Put in oven and bake 45 minutes.

title: cornell sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Use as marinade for skinless chicken breasts.
Drain briefly, grill quickly.
Enough for 6 to 8 split chicken breasts.

title: fried rice(special)
directions: Make a thin omelet with the beaten eggs and cut into strips; put aside.
Sprinkle water on the cooked rice to loosen the grains.
Set aside.
Heat the oil and saute garlic and onion.
Add chicken, pork and shrimp and continue cooking until light brown. Add cooked rice and soy sauce.
Toss mixture over low heat for 8 minutes until thoroughly mixed.
Add sweet peas, half of the egg strips.
salt and pepper.
Toss for 2 minutes more and remove from fire.
Serve on platter and sprinkle top with green onions and rest of egg strips.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix the cake mix as directed. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Drop the coconut and nuts onto the bottom of the pan. Pour cake mix in.

title: easy taco dip
directions: Mix until well blended.
Chill.
Serve with chips or vegetables.
Yields 3 cups.

title: stilton soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add vegetables, fry gently for 5 minutes.
Stir in the flour and cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in wine and stock.
Return to heat, bring to boil and simmer 30 minutes.
Add milk and cheeses, stirring constantly. Season; stir in fresh cream.
Rub through sieve or puree in blender.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake Mexican Cornbread according to directions.
Mix ranch dressing, sour cream and mayonnaise together.
Crumble half of cornbread on bottom of large bowl. Layer
half of corn, pinto beans, vegetables and cheese.
Spread half of dressing over vegetable layer.
Repeat layering. Top with remaining cheese and bacon bits, if desired.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix the ingredients and keep in a tightly covered jar.
Use one or two teaspoons to one cup of hot water.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in electric skillet.
Slice onion over chicken. Add Coke, then catsup.
Cover and cook at 325° with vent open. Turn chicken every 15 minutes.
Cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until liquid cooks out.

title: fresno chicken
directions: Beat chicken breasts to 1/4 inch thickness.
Drain chiles and olives and mix with cheeses and onion.
